WEBVTT

00:10.719 --> 00:13.929
[♪♪♪]

00:31.865 --> 00:33.615
[BELL TOLLING]

00:40.123 --> 00:42.708
[ROOSTER CROWS]

01:06.274 --> 01:08.150
[SNORING]

01:25.460 --> 01:26.668
Darling?

01:27.253 --> 01:29.213
[SNORING]

02:03.748 --> 02:05.874
Oh, darling.

02:06.042 --> 02:07.793
[SNORING]

02:13.883 --> 02:16.176
[♪♪♪]

02:32.110 --> 02:34.027
But sex.

02:34.195 --> 02:36.029
You are 23.

02:36.197 --> 02:39.199
Not an easy age
for abstinence, is it?

02:39.367 --> 02:41.410
Tolstoy does not approve
of sexual relations.

02:41.578 --> 02:43.704
I know this.
He despises them, in fact.

02:45.039 --> 02:47.291
Well, l don't mean
to belabor the point,

02:47.458 --> 02:50.919
but last summer
I arranged for a manservant

02:51.087 --> 02:53.922
who proceeded to ruin
two housemaids, just like that.

02:54.090 --> 02:55.132
He was very upset.

02:55.300 --> 02:58.051
This would not be a problem
with me. I'm a vegetarian.

02:58.219 --> 02:59.636
I am celibate.

02:59.804 --> 03:01.346
I'm also a vegetarian.

03:01.514 --> 03:05.475
My dear boy, if you were to become
Tolstoy's private secretary,

03:05.643 --> 03:07.269
you would be given a great gift.

03:07.437 --> 03:09.188
Vladimir Grigorevich,
please know

03:09.355 --> 03:13.400
that I understand
what a privilege this
position presents.

03:13.568 --> 03:18.071
But since becoming a Tolstoyan,
I have become so eager to learn,

03:18.239 --> 03:20.949
to discuss ideas,
to perfect my very soul.

03:21.117 --> 03:23.577
Yes. Well...

03:23.745 --> 03:27.956
We have a lot to do
if we are to get his
work to the people.

03:28.124 --> 03:30.000
We?
Yes, we.

03:30.168 --> 03:31.877
[LAUGHS]

03:32.045 --> 03:35.047
If we can encourage the spread
of passive resistance,

03:35.215 --> 03:37.633
just think of it, Valentin.

03:37.800 --> 03:40.886
Thousands of ordinary
Russians

03:41.471 --> 03:44.598
casting off centuries of political
and spiritual oppression.

03:44.766 --> 03:48.852
In the name of truth and freedom.
Truth and freedom. Yes, yes.

03:49.020 --> 03:52.814
But, still, there are
many, many enemies.

03:52.982 --> 03:55.442
Enemies?
Come.

03:55.610 --> 03:57.694
The czar's police.

03:57.862 --> 03:59.905
Now, you will be followed
when you leave here,

04:00.073 --> 04:03.492
and the Church will stop at nothing
to bring him back into the fold.

04:03.952 --> 04:06.745
And then, of course,
there is the countess.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.457
Her dogged attachment
to private property,

04:10.625 --> 04:12.918
her public criticism
of our movement.

04:13.086 --> 04:14.586
[SIGHS]

04:14.796 --> 04:16.338
But the point is

04:16.505 --> 04:19.298
he needs a man of your
intellectual gifts around him.

04:19.466 --> 04:21.510
Someone who understands
his goals.

04:21.678 --> 04:23.845
And they still won't
let me see him.

04:24.013 --> 04:26.265
They keep me under
house arrest.

04:27.976 --> 04:31.770
I have another task for you,
my dear.

04:32.313 --> 04:36.358
I want you to keep
a diary for me.

04:37.527 --> 04:40.612
I need to know what goes on
at Yasnaya Polyana.

04:40.780 --> 04:41.863
Mm-hm.

04:42.031 --> 04:43.991
You let me know
who visits the house,

04:44.158 --> 04:47.828
any talk of the copyright to his work,
any contact with the Church,

04:47.996 --> 04:50.205
anything the countess says.

04:50.373 --> 04:53.041
Anything?
She's very, very dangerous.

04:53.209 --> 04:55.127
[♪♪♪]

04:55.920 --> 04:57.087
[CHERTKOV SHOUTS]

04:57.255 --> 04:59.673
DRIVER:
Whoa, whoa.

05:00.717 --> 05:02.050
Godspeed, my boy.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.553
And remember what I said.
Mm-hm.

05:04.721 --> 05:07.681
Write everything down.

05:08.975 --> 05:10.100
Driver!

05:10.268 --> 05:12.352
DRIVER:
Walk on. Whoa, whoa.

05:29.078 --> 05:31.079
[PEOPLE CHATTERlNG]

05:35.877 --> 05:36.918
REPORTER:
Good morning, countess.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.463
Are you rolling? Are you rolling?
CAMERMAN: l am.

05:39.630 --> 05:42.424
CINEMATOGRAPHER:
Countess? Countess?

05:45.261 --> 05:46.553
[FLASHBULB POPS]

05:47.764 --> 05:48.805
It doesn't matter.

05:48.973 --> 05:51.516
If my heart stopped beating,
I'd still go riding today.

05:51.684 --> 05:53.143
Your pulse is
my responsibility.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.228
No. It's mine.
Fine.

05:55.396 --> 05:57.356
If you must ride,
I insist you wear a coat.

05:57.523 --> 05:59.274
Even the sun is cold today.
SOFYA: Oh, this!

05:59.442 --> 06:03.070
This is impossible!
These people are parasites!

06:04.072 --> 06:06.823
"The Countess Tolstoy
is estranged from her husband.

06:06.991 --> 06:09.409
They barely speak."

06:09.577 --> 06:11.620
And they gossip
about us in Paris.

06:11.788 --> 06:14.456
"They do not share
a similar view of
religion or politics."

06:14.624 --> 06:15.957
You think that's inaccurate?

06:16.125 --> 06:18.085
I think it's none
of the world's
bloody business.

06:18.252 --> 06:20.796
What are you doing?
Why do you write down
everything we say?

06:20.963 --> 06:22.047
Don't do that.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.966
TOLSTOY:
Dushan Petrovich,
you are scribbling again.

06:25.134 --> 06:26.802
[CHUCKLES]

06:26.969 --> 06:29.513
Oh, Leovochka,
why do you insist on
dressing like that?

06:29.680 --> 06:32.808
What do you mean, like what?
Like the man who looks after sheep.

06:32.975 --> 06:34.976
TOLSTOY:
It wasn't meant to offend you.

06:35.144 --> 06:37.938
You're a count, for God's sake.

06:38.398 --> 06:39.731
Darling,
where are you going?

06:39.899 --> 06:42.442
Riding with Sasha.
Don't expect us for lunch.

06:42.610 --> 06:44.653
DUSHAN: Lev Nikolayevich,
you've forgotten your coat.

06:44.821 --> 06:45.987
TOLSTOY:
Dushan, are you fretting?

06:46.155 --> 06:48.990
DUSHAN:
Yes, because you refuse
to look after yourself.

06:49.617 --> 06:51.701
[♪♪♪]

07:05.842 --> 07:08.385
[TRAIN BELL CLANGING]

07:09.220 --> 07:11.138
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLARES]

07:13.015 --> 07:15.183
[CHATTERING lN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

07:22.233 --> 07:23.525
[SIGHS]

07:34.370 --> 07:37.122
MAN: Telyatinki was created
by Vladimir Grigorevich

07:37.290 --> 07:39.374
as a center for the movement.

07:39.542 --> 07:44.045
We're all equals here, you know,
as Tolstoy teaches us.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.298
This is a place of freedom.

07:51.387 --> 07:53.096
It's a beautiful day.

07:53.264 --> 07:55.682
Yes, but we'll pay for it.

07:57.059 --> 07:58.226
Toolshed is there.

07:58.394 --> 08:01.605
That's the meeting room,
and this is the dormitory.

08:01.814 --> 08:03.148
WOMAN:
I found it!

08:03.900 --> 08:05.817
Afternoon.
Yes, hello.

08:05.985 --> 08:08.612
You are expected
at Yasnaya Polyana
in the morning,

08:08.779 --> 08:10.155
first thing.
First thing?

08:10.323 --> 08:12.949
You'll need to be on the road early.
It's nearly two hours away.

08:13.117 --> 08:16.870
I look forward to it.
Yes. You're lucky.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.413
We're all envious.

08:27.006 --> 08:28.840
I'll see you in the morning.

08:29.300 --> 08:31.092
If we're spared.

08:38.851 --> 08:40.184
Right.

08:40.352 --> 08:43.020
And out.

08:44.982 --> 08:46.483
In.

08:49.070 --> 08:52.280
MAN: Emma, can you come?
We need you in the house.

08:52.615 --> 08:54.199
[KNOCKlNG ON DOOR]

08:58.454 --> 08:59.621
Come in.

08:59.789 --> 09:01.373
[DOOR OPENS]

09:05.086 --> 09:08.421
Brought you a glass of tea.
That's very kind of you.

09:11.926 --> 09:14.261
It's your first day.

09:14.428 --> 09:16.054
Enjoy it.

09:21.644 --> 09:23.436
You met Sergeyenko?

09:24.480 --> 09:26.189
Last night, yes.

09:27.733 --> 09:29.276
What do you think?

09:29.443 --> 09:31.695
I thought he seemed
very sincere.

09:31.862 --> 09:32.904
Thank you.

09:33.072 --> 09:34.364
[LAUGHS]

09:34.532 --> 09:35.907
What?

09:36.075 --> 09:38.660
Is that what you think?
I think that...

09:40.621 --> 09:43.999
I think I've just arrived.
What was your name?

09:44.166 --> 09:47.460
Masha. But you should
still say what you think.

09:47.628 --> 09:49.838
I mean, not just about him.

09:50.006 --> 09:51.172
Like we all should.

09:52.967 --> 09:54.009
Yes.

09:57.179 --> 09:58.346
[SNEEZES]

09:59.807 --> 10:01.141
Excuse me.

10:04.812 --> 10:06.479
Thank you for the tea.

10:12.862 --> 10:15.739
He's a sorry, old, tight-assed
stick-in-the-mud,

10:15.906 --> 10:18.992
but, yes, he's sincere.

10:25.958 --> 10:27.959
[♪♪♪]

11:06.874 --> 11:08.416
Hello?

11:11.253 --> 11:12.629
MAN:
Out of the way.

11:15.424 --> 11:17.050
Hello?

11:18.386 --> 11:20.929
Ah. Excuse me.

11:21.097 --> 11:22.263
SASHA:
You.

11:22.431 --> 11:24.432
You're the new secretary?
Yes.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.434
Valentin Fedorovich Bulgakov.

11:26.602 --> 11:30.188
Papa is out. You can wait
upstairs in the library.

11:33.359 --> 11:35.360
[♪♪♪]

12:08.185 --> 12:09.310
[DOOR OPENS]

12:10.646 --> 12:13.815
I am so glad you're here.

12:13.983 --> 12:15.483
[LAUGHS]

12:17.528 --> 12:19.446
I'm so glad.

12:20.865 --> 12:22.282
[SNEEZES]

12:22.450 --> 12:26.077
God bless you.
Pardon me. l'm mortified.

12:26.245 --> 12:28.163
I sneeze sometimes
when l get nervous.

12:28.330 --> 12:29.831
[CHUCKLES]

12:30.750 --> 12:32.709
Yes.

12:32.877 --> 12:36.254
Now, Vladimir Grigorevich
has already written about
you at lengths.

12:36.464 --> 12:40.341
I don't need that.
What l do need is your help.

12:40.509 --> 12:43.178
My manifesto against
the government is hard work.

12:43.345 --> 12:47.932
They commit their idiotic abuses
faster than I can catalog them.

12:48.100 --> 12:49.225
Yes.

12:49.393 --> 12:51.770
And then there's the new book,
the compendium.

12:51.937 --> 12:53.605
Vladimir Grigorevich
told me all about it.

12:53.773 --> 12:57.525
He says that you say that
all the world's religions
share common truths.

12:57.693 --> 12:59.360
It's very exciting.
No, one truth.

12:59.528 --> 13:03.364
One single organizing principle.
And can you guess what that is?

13:03.908 --> 13:05.867
Um...
Eh?

13:06.035 --> 13:09.370
Love. Love. Simple.

13:10.539 --> 13:12.624
Yeah, but l want
to talk about you.

13:13.417 --> 13:15.752
How are you?
And how was your journey?

13:15.920 --> 13:17.462
Come, sit down.

13:17.963 --> 13:22.258
I was born on that sofa.
No, no, sit, sit.

13:22.426 --> 13:25.637
Myself, my brother, my children,

13:25.805 --> 13:28.306
five or six of them, at least.
Right here.

13:28.474 --> 13:29.808
Congratulations.

13:32.436 --> 13:35.688
Well, l've read your essays.

13:36.690 --> 13:39.025
How's the work progressing?

13:39.193 --> 13:40.235
[CHUCKLES]

13:40.402 --> 13:43.071
[STAMMERlNG]

13:45.115 --> 13:47.242
My boy, what is it?

13:48.452 --> 13:50.912
Oh, l've upset you in some way.
No.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.748
Was it the sofa?
I mean, it's only a sofa.

13:53.916 --> 13:55.875
The sofa's wonderful.

13:56.919 --> 13:57.961
I...

13:58.128 --> 14:00.338
I'm very happy.
Mm-hm.

14:00.506 --> 14:03.091
You're very kind to me.

14:04.927 --> 14:07.178
You see, I am no one,

14:07.346 --> 14:10.473
and you are Lev Tolstoy.

14:10.641 --> 14:13.893
And you ask me
about my work.

14:14.061 --> 14:16.896
I'll fetch you a glass of tea.

14:17.064 --> 14:18.773
Yes.
Now, you rest.

14:18.941 --> 14:20.108
[♪♪♪]

14:20.276 --> 14:24.863
Yeah, because there's work
for both of us to do, together!

14:25.030 --> 14:28.116
Yes.

14:29.076 --> 14:30.577
God.

14:32.246 --> 14:35.373
This machine, it really is
the most extraordinary thing.

14:35.541 --> 14:37.292
SASHA:
Mama, these people have nothing.

14:37.459 --> 14:40.336
No, it's not for lack of land
that the muzhiks live in poverty.

14:40.504 --> 14:43.131
It's because they
have no willpower and
they drink too much.

14:43.299 --> 14:46.593
I am not suggesting
they be given land.

14:46.760 --> 14:48.761
Private property is the root
of the problem.

14:48.929 --> 14:51.806
We should be giving ours away.
God. Giving it to whom?

14:51.974 --> 14:54.058
Yes, exactly.
I mean, this is ridiculous.

14:54.226 --> 14:57.312
You think because the
peasants are poor, they're
somehow morally superior.

14:57.479 --> 14:59.564
I believe that wealth
corrupts us all.

14:59.732 --> 15:00.815
Yes, l do.

15:00.983 --> 15:02.984
Mm. lt's a keystone
of the movement.

15:03.152 --> 15:05.153
Oh, God, l know
all about the movement.

15:06.363 --> 15:07.947
If the peasants
had money,

15:08.115 --> 15:10.408
they wouldn't surround
themselves, as we do,

15:10.576 --> 15:12.744
with footmen costing
1 0 rubles a month.

15:12.912 --> 15:15.997
No, they'd spend it
on drink and whores.

15:16.707 --> 15:19.000
Valentin Fedorovich.
Mm.

15:19.168 --> 15:20.501
What do you think?
Tea.

15:20.669 --> 15:24.589
You think that 50 years
from now, people will eat
while grown men walk around

15:24.757 --> 15:26.841
waiting on them
hand and foot?

15:27.009 --> 15:28.176
I th-- I think--
That's good.

15:29.094 --> 15:30.136
[SNEEZES]

15:30.304 --> 15:32.597
Bless you.
Stop scribbling.

15:32.765 --> 15:35.475
I mean, you all think
he's Christ, don't you?

15:35.643 --> 15:39.062
He thinks he's Christ.
I'm not...

15:39.605 --> 15:42.440
I don't believe
Lev Nikolayevich
is Christ.

15:42.608 --> 15:44.359
Christ is Christ,
but, uh...

15:44.526 --> 15:45.777
But what?

15:45.945 --> 15:48.154
I do believe
he's one of the prophets.

15:48.322 --> 15:49.656
God speaks through him.

15:49.823 --> 15:51.616
I recognize the cadence
in his voice.

15:51.784 --> 15:53.660
Oh, God, this is unbearable.

15:53.827 --> 15:56.955
No wonder I feel lonely.
I'm surrounded by morons.

15:57.122 --> 15:59.832
Ma, you're being ridiculous.
SOFYA: Oh, am l?

16:00.000 --> 16:03.962
I have to sit here and listen
to this talk of love and God
and equality,

16:04.129 --> 16:06.506
knowing all the time,
full well,

16:06.674 --> 16:09.676
that Count Generosity
here is about to give away
everything we own.

16:09.843 --> 16:12.971
Now, why do you keep
going on about this?

16:13.138 --> 16:16.683
Why do you think that
we should profit from
the work I'm doing now?

16:16.850 --> 16:18.977
Which is only meant
for the sake of the people.

16:20.020 --> 16:21.688
Stop writing!

16:22.106 --> 16:26.192
Stop writing now!

16:38.622 --> 16:41.874
In defense of my gift,
please let me demonstrate.

16:42.042 --> 16:44.043
It's quite remarkable, really.

16:49.842 --> 16:53.428
TOLSTOY [OVER GRAMOPHONE]:
In the same way now,
a society of hunger,

16:53.595 --> 16:56.264
full of segregation...

16:57.725 --> 16:58.766
l understand,

16:58.934 --> 17:02.729
not only with my mind, or heart,
VALENTIN: lt's-- lt's your voice.

17:02.896 --> 17:05.606
but with my soul,
that the existence

17:05.773 --> 17:07.775
of tens of thousands...
It's your voice.

17:07.943 --> 17:09.777
It's wonderful.
It's wonderful!

17:10.612 --> 17:12.238
It's tiresome.

17:13.031 --> 17:15.366
Another remarkable invention
will supersede it.

17:15.534 --> 17:17.492
Please excuse me.

17:18.704 --> 17:21.914
No matter what all the learned men
in the world say...

17:22.082 --> 17:24.791
Lev Nikolayevich is
something of a Luddite, l fear.

17:24.960 --> 17:26.794
It is a crime.

17:26.962 --> 17:31.257
And one committed not once,
but constantly.

17:31.425 --> 17:34.302
I knew that I, with my luxury--

17:34.470 --> 17:35.928
[GRAMOPHONE STOPS]

17:42.144 --> 17:45.646
[MOZART'S "GENTE, GENTE,
ALL'ARMI, ALL'ARMl" PLAYlNG
OVER GRAMOPHONE]

18:00.079 --> 18:01.162
That's better.

18:05.292 --> 18:06.918
That's nice.

18:16.303 --> 18:18.346
That's very nice indeed.

18:52.381 --> 18:55.341
Do your parents often speak
to each other so bluntly?

18:55.509 --> 18:58.553
Mama doesn't understand
my father's goals,

18:58.720 --> 19:01.764
not since his work as a novelist
became secondary.

19:01.932 --> 19:06.519
His commitment to the
spiritual life offends her.

19:06.687 --> 19:09.397
They've fought
about it for years.

19:09.565 --> 19:12.275
Well, l'm sure
she means well by it.

19:15.487 --> 19:19.782
I see a fine young man
before me. Clear eyes,
nice features,

19:19.950 --> 19:22.201
rather handsome
in a peculiar sort of a way.

19:22.369 --> 19:23.744
Th-- Thank you,
countess.

19:23.912 --> 19:25.913
Oh, please, call me
Sofya Andreyevna.

19:26.081 --> 19:30.126
We don't stand on formality here,
as you may have noticed.

19:30.294 --> 19:32.086
No, no. So many
young men nowadays

19:32.254 --> 19:36.632
spoil their good looks
with loose living, but you...

19:36.800 --> 19:41.262
Ooh, you're a real
Tolstoyan, I can tell that.

19:41.430 --> 19:44.432
Well, thank you. l have to say,
I admire your husband immensely.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.225
Oh, very good.

19:46.393 --> 19:48.603
Excellent. He likes that.

19:48.770 --> 19:52.356
Well, his ideas are beautiful.
Social justice, the very concept--

19:52.524 --> 19:55.318
Yes, yes, he's very
grateful for the help
you've been giving him.

19:55.485 --> 19:57.778
He told me that himself.
I think he's rather surprised

19:57.946 --> 20:00.448
that a young man like you
can be quite so diligent.

20:00.616 --> 20:03.034
You know, when he was
your age, he was whoring
in the Caucasus.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.411
Couldn't get enough of it.

20:05.662 --> 20:08.080
Yes, he wrote all about it.

20:08.248 --> 20:12.710
He even gave me a copy,
so l could read all the details.

20:12.878 --> 20:15.796
Would you like some more jam?
Yes, thank you.

20:15.964 --> 20:19.050
Have you read War and Peace?
Yes, many times.

20:19.218 --> 20:20.468
Hmm.

20:21.053 --> 20:22.637
Twice.

20:22.804 --> 20:23.846
[CHUCKLES]

20:24.014 --> 20:26.641
You know,
when Lev was writing it--
Oh, this was ages ago,

20:26.808 --> 20:30.645
long before Chertkov
created that monstrosity
at Telyatinki,

20:30.812 --> 20:35.274
over all that fake religion
and revolutionary nonsense.

20:35.734 --> 20:37.652
What do you think of
Chertkov, by the way?

20:37.819 --> 20:39.070
Well, l think that he's...

20:39.238 --> 20:41.155
[STAMMERS]

20:42.241 --> 20:44.033
I think he's given me
a wonderful opportunity.

20:44.201 --> 20:46.494
Yes, but you can see
what a pompous fool he is,

20:46.662 --> 20:49.914
what a self-serving
puritanical idiot.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.833
I must say, it's been very
pleasant since he's been
locked away in his house.

20:53.001 --> 20:54.293
Right.

20:55.545 --> 20:58.506
So, anyway, when he was
writing it, in the mid-'60s,

20:58.674 --> 21:01.509
he used to bring me pages
to copy every day

21:01.677 --> 21:05.137
because l was the only one
who could understand his
handwriting or his notes.

21:05.305 --> 21:07.723
Do you know I copied out
War and Peace six times?

21:07.891 --> 21:09.850
Six times?

21:10.185 --> 21:12.895
I could understand
his intentions too.

21:13.063 --> 21:17.024
So every afternoon, we'd have tea
and we'd discuss changes.

21:17.192 --> 21:18.234
And l'd say to him,

21:18.402 --> 21:22.113
"You know, Natasha wouldn't
speak to Prince Andrei like that.
No woman would."

21:22.281 --> 21:25.116
Or, "Pierre's too simple here.
He's not an idiot."

21:25.284 --> 21:26.993
You know,
things like that.

21:27.160 --> 21:28.369
[CHUCKLES]

21:31.581 --> 21:34.000
But I don't count anymore.

21:36.712 --> 21:37.753
[FOOTSTEPS]

21:44.386 --> 21:45.720
[DOOR CLOSES]

21:48.473 --> 21:50.474
[♪♪♪]

21:54.938 --> 21:57.565
You must help me,
Vladimir Fedorovich.

21:57.733 --> 21:59.900
Oh, Valentin Fedorovich.

22:00.068 --> 22:02.528
I only want what's best for
my husband and my family.

22:02.696 --> 22:05.531
If it was for me alone,
I could tolerate the situation,

22:05.699 --> 22:08.993
but I cannot stand by
while they steal my
children's inheritance.

22:09.161 --> 22:12.413
Well, l don't believe anybody
wants to do that.

22:12.581 --> 22:14.332
I don't. I mean...

22:14.499 --> 22:16.917
Theft goes against the very
principles of Tolstoyan thought.

22:17.085 --> 22:19.337
I have a little gift
for you.

22:21.381 --> 22:23.424
You--?
Mm.

22:24.718 --> 22:26.469
It's a diary.

22:26.636 --> 22:29.930
You know, everyone
should always keep a diary.

22:31.308 --> 22:33.684
Yes, it's a very popular
activity around here.

22:33.852 --> 22:35.102
You're teasing us.

22:35.937 --> 22:38.272
But I trust you'll
write the truth.

22:39.316 --> 22:41.108
Well, that may
not be so easy.

22:41.276 --> 22:44.278
Oh, nonsense.
You've been listening to
your friends at Telyatinki.

22:44.446 --> 22:47.615
No, no, just write what
you see around you.

22:48.867 --> 22:51.118
What you see.

22:52.537 --> 22:53.579
[SNEEZES]

22:57.626 --> 23:00.086
[PANTlNG]

23:01.630 --> 23:02.797
[GRUNTS]

23:09.471 --> 23:12.056
You're finished
for the day?

23:12.224 --> 23:14.392
Yes, he didn't need me
this afternoon.

23:14.559 --> 23:18.145
I thought I'd come back here

23:18.313 --> 23:19.939
and lend a hand.

23:23.443 --> 23:26.612
You know, Lev Nikolayevich
considers himself a liberal

23:26.780 --> 23:30.199
but he doesn't approve of
women doing physical labor.

23:32.160 --> 23:34.245
Don't you find that reactionary?
No.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.122
I find it sweet.

23:37.499 --> 23:39.458
I find you reactionary.

23:41.586 --> 23:42.670
[LAUGHS]

23:44.756 --> 23:47.007
What do you talk about
when you're with him?

23:48.427 --> 23:49.802
We, uh...

23:52.389 --> 23:54.348
Why are you blushing?
I'm not.

23:57.727 --> 23:58.769
We talk about me.

23:59.813 --> 24:02.106
Really?
Yes.

24:02.274 --> 24:04.692
He wants to know about
my family, my upbringing.

24:04.860 --> 24:07.027
My connection to God
and my relations with women.

24:07.195 --> 24:08.446
Ooh.

24:09.072 --> 24:11.365
What relations
are these?

24:26.214 --> 24:28.424
All right, it's all right.

24:35.056 --> 24:37.600
[GRUNTlNG]

24:45.984 --> 24:47.026
Phew.

24:47.694 --> 24:48.986
Well done.

24:56.453 --> 24:59.371
I had a lover
before I came here.

24:59.664 --> 25:03.042
He was headmaster of
the school where I taught.

25:03.668 --> 25:05.753
He was married.

25:05.921 --> 25:10.216
He was happily married.
It was difficult.

25:10.383 --> 25:12.051
We could make love
only at school.

25:12.219 --> 25:13.761
At school?

25:13.929 --> 25:17.097
In the gymnasium,
after the girls had gone.

25:17.265 --> 25:19.767
I see. I see.

25:22.896 --> 25:25.523
Oh! There you are.
Have l upset you?

25:26.024 --> 25:27.525
No.

25:29.277 --> 25:33.072
No, I find you...
I-- l appreciate
your frankness.

25:33.240 --> 25:34.823
But you disapprove of me?
No!

25:34.991 --> 25:37.785
I see it in your eyes.
Not at all.

25:38.078 --> 25:42.289
No. Pfft. I think
sexual behavior

25:42.457 --> 25:43.874
and intercourse,

25:44.042 --> 25:46.794
how two men,
or two women,

25:46.962 --> 25:48.754
or men and women,

25:48.922 --> 25:51.006
animals,
combine their physical parts,

25:51.174 --> 25:52.925
I find it completely neutral.

25:53.093 --> 25:54.969
[LAUGHS]

25:55.136 --> 25:56.887
Listen to you.

25:57.055 --> 25:59.390
You're a prig.

25:59.558 --> 26:03.477
You're just like Sergeyenko.
I mean, why else would they
have hired you?

26:03.645 --> 26:05.437
That's not fair.

26:05.605 --> 26:07.273
I don't care if it's fair.
It's true.

26:08.316 --> 26:09.316
That's it.

26:10.694 --> 26:14.029
I'm going.
Do as you like.

26:14.197 --> 26:16.699
[♪♪♪]

26:16.866 --> 26:19.326
Valentin
Fedorovich?

26:19.995 --> 26:21.120
Yes?

26:22.706 --> 26:23.998
You forgot
your horse.

26:26.001 --> 26:27.001
Yes.

26:58.408 --> 27:00.117
Where's Papa?

27:02.871 --> 27:07.124
TOLSTOY:
I had a dream last night,
about a Tartar girl l knew in the war.

27:07.667 --> 27:08.751
A girl who died?

27:08.918 --> 27:12.004
No, no, no. Just a girl
I had sexual intercourse with.

27:12.172 --> 27:13.380
Oh?

27:13.548 --> 27:16.091
Sometimes, we did it
twice a day.

27:16.468 --> 27:17.509
[SNEEZES]

27:17.677 --> 27:18.719
God bless you.

27:19.304 --> 27:22.181
I've never forgotten
our time together.

27:22.349 --> 27:25.893
The positions of our bodies,
and the taste of her.

27:26.061 --> 27:28.854
It was a long time ago.
Really, you mustn't
torture yourself.

27:29.022 --> 27:31.857
Torture? You are a virgin,
aren't you?

27:32.025 --> 27:34.193
Well, l try to be.
I mean, I try to be--

27:34.361 --> 27:36.111
To what,
to be a good Tolstoyan?

27:36.279 --> 27:39.823
Let me assure you that
I'm not a very good
Tolstoyan myself.

27:39.991 --> 27:44.828
You should think twice
before asking my advice
on anything.

27:45.789 --> 27:47.247
"Torture."

27:47.415 --> 27:50.209
[LAUGHING]

27:59.469 --> 28:01.762
Kalya was her name.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.099
She's an old woman now.

28:05.266 --> 28:08.852
White hair, old body,
like me.

28:09.020 --> 28:11.438
Hardly remember
my name, I suspect.

28:11.606 --> 28:13.732
She may even be dead.

28:15.360 --> 28:17.736
Do you think all that
meant something?

28:17.904 --> 28:18.946
What do you mean?

28:19.114 --> 28:21.115
Well, l mean,
that little romance.

28:22.075 --> 28:24.368
Was there
some meaning to it?

28:24.536 --> 28:26.787
Well, l think you
would say--

28:26.955 --> 28:31.083
I mean, I think I've read
where you say that the
physical body is not real.

28:31.251 --> 28:32.668
That it's all
an illusion.

28:32.836 --> 28:35.754
Oh, l say a lot of things.
But what do you say?

28:36.423 --> 28:38.173
What do you think?

28:40.135 --> 28:41.927
I don't know.

28:43.888 --> 28:45.973
I don't know, either.

28:48.351 --> 28:50.185
Oh, smell that.

28:51.062 --> 28:54.648
Lilac.
Precisely. Lilac.

28:54.816 --> 28:56.775
Scent gets stronger
when the sun goes down.

28:56.943 --> 28:58.318
Does it?

28:59.112 --> 29:00.738
SASHA:
Papa!

29:00.905 --> 29:02.906
[♪♪♪]

29:04.826 --> 29:08.871
He's free!

29:09.622 --> 29:11.081
He's coming back!

29:23.803 --> 29:25.012
[FLASHBULB POPS]

29:28.558 --> 29:30.392
My friend.

29:31.770 --> 29:35.230
SOFYA: He has come
to try again to persuade
your father to change the will,

29:35.398 --> 29:38.275
to give the copyright
as a gift to humanity.

29:38.443 --> 29:40.444
The reptile.
Papa's not in his right mind.

29:40.612 --> 29:42.696
He can't defend himself
against these thieves.

29:42.864 --> 29:44.990
You're a fine son, my darling.

29:45.158 --> 29:47.701
None of this fake chastity
or made-up religion.

29:48.536 --> 29:51.622
I wish all my children
had turned out like you.

29:53.500 --> 29:57.252
Vladimir Grigorevich,
what a surprise.

29:57.420 --> 29:59.296
Sofya Andreyevna.

29:59.464 --> 30:03.300
I'm happy to see you.
And l'm happy to make you happy.

30:03.468 --> 30:04.718
[CHUCKLES]

30:04.886 --> 30:07.054
TOLSTOY:
Come, come, my friend.

30:07.222 --> 30:10.390
Now, we have a great deal
to talk about.

30:16.189 --> 30:19.024
CHERTKOV:
I'm happy to have a moment
alone with you, Valentin.

30:19.192 --> 30:22.236
There seems to be some confusion.
What do you mean?

30:22.403 --> 30:24.655
Well, you send me neverending
commentary on Tolstoy's writing,

30:24.823 --> 30:28.158
and that's all very interesting,
but not very useful.

30:28.326 --> 30:31.578
See, l need to know what
goes on with Sofya Andreyevna.

30:32.038 --> 30:33.997
You must see by now
how committed she is

30:34.165 --> 30:36.542
to undermining her husband's
best intentions.

30:36.709 --> 30:38.752
It's not quite so obvious to me.

30:39.337 --> 30:42.506
The woman understands
nothing of what we're doing.

30:43.216 --> 30:45.467
We simply want to distribute
Tolstoy's writing

30:45.635 --> 30:48.011
to the widest audience
possible.

30:49.430 --> 30:52.140
[WHlSPERlNG]
I can only be of limited use
to the master

30:52.308 --> 30:54.560
if l don't know
what's going on.

30:55.311 --> 30:59.022
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
The survival of our movement
depends upon it.

30:59.399 --> 31:01.567
You value our work?
I do.

31:01.734 --> 31:05.195
The ideals we share?
It's why l'm here.

31:06.531 --> 31:08.323
Very good.

31:14.247 --> 31:17.249
[♪♪♪]

31:32.181 --> 31:35.475
Good morning, darling.
Good morning.

31:35.810 --> 31:39.897
Do you mind if I join you?
No, of course, of course, my dear.

32:01.794 --> 32:03.503
You know,

32:03.671 --> 32:07.841
it's quite insane,
my darling, how people
are making fun of you.

32:08.009 --> 32:10.302
Hm? What are you talking about?
Even the muzhiks.

32:10.470 --> 32:12.846
I heard them laughing
about it in the horse barn.

32:13.014 --> 32:14.848
Hm? About what?

32:15.016 --> 32:17.017
Laughing about what?

32:20.396 --> 32:22.898
About the fact that you've
developed a senile crush

32:23.066 --> 32:25.400
on a fat,
middle-aged flatterer.

32:25.568 --> 32:28.320
Your passion for Chertkov
has become a standing joke.

32:28.488 --> 32:31.114
I have a great affection
for Vladimir Grigorevich.

32:31.282 --> 32:33.533
Let them laugh
if they find it so amusing.

32:33.701 --> 32:36.828
It's not amusing, darling.
It's sick. It's not normal.

32:36.996 --> 32:38.830
I mean, you hang on
his every word.

32:38.998 --> 32:40.540
We have a great deal
in common.

32:40.708 --> 32:42.876
You have nothing
in common.

32:43.044 --> 32:46.463
You are a genius, and he is
a sycophant and a pervert.

32:46.631 --> 32:49.341
Because he understands
what I'm trying to do?

32:49.509 --> 32:51.426
Because he tries to
help me accomplish it?

32:51.594 --> 32:54.554
He's just using you.
You just can't seem to see it.

32:54.722 --> 32:55.973
Oh, this is
absolute nonsense.

32:56.140 --> 32:59.226
That bald, obese, idiotic man, you--
It is impossible for you

32:59.394 --> 33:00.727
not to distract me!

33:01.229 --> 33:05.065
Now, leave me alone, for God's sake.
You're like a spoiled child.

33:07.902 --> 33:11.029
Do you love me, Leovochka?
Of course I do.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.240
Then why do you
betray me like this?

33:13.408 --> 33:15.242
Why do you say that?

33:15.576 --> 33:17.661
Because of the will.

33:17.954 --> 33:19.496
The new will.

33:19.664 --> 33:21.248
[♪♪♪]

33:21.416 --> 33:23.417
There's no new will.

33:23.710 --> 33:25.919
Does Chertkov have it?
There is no new will.

33:26.087 --> 33:28.005
Yes, but that's why
he's here, isn't it?

33:28.172 --> 33:31.133
You talk about it,
you and your boyfriend.
You plan for it.

33:31.300 --> 33:33.760
You have no heart
for the people who
really love you.

33:33.928 --> 33:37.305
You'd rather be seduced
by charlatans and deluded
by flatterers,

33:37.473 --> 33:41.101
all in the name of love.
You can't even love
your own children.

33:41.269 --> 33:43.603
You can't even love me.
Where is it?

33:43.771 --> 33:45.939
There is no new will!

33:46.107 --> 33:48.191
Then promise me
there never will be.

33:52.613 --> 33:56.408
I have told you the truth.

33:58.036 --> 33:59.953
Now let me work.

34:01.247 --> 34:02.748
Will you?

34:02.957 --> 34:05.292
[♪♪♪]

34:08.004 --> 34:11.005
Fine, I'll go to the station
and l'll throw myself under a train.

34:11.174 --> 34:13.175
Madam Tolstoy
becomes Anna Karenina.

34:13.342 --> 34:14.717
See how the press
will like that.

34:14.886 --> 34:18.388
Oh, this is unbearable.
You don't need a husband,
you need a Greek chorus!

34:25.353 --> 34:27.355
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

34:28.608 --> 34:30.609
[RAINDROPS PATTERING]

34:34.947 --> 34:36.281
[DOOR OPENS]

34:40.078 --> 34:41.745
Masha--?
Shh.

35:12.318 --> 35:14.611
Masha--
Shh.

35:38.136 --> 35:39.803
Mmph!
Hm?

35:39.971 --> 35:41.138
Move your book.

35:41.305 --> 35:43.390
What?
Your book.

35:43.558 --> 35:47.227
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Ahem.

36:05.413 --> 36:06.913
[VALENTIN MOANS]

36:08.166 --> 36:09.416
Is it okay?

36:09.584 --> 36:10.625
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

36:10.793 --> 36:12.294
Yeah?
Mm-hm.

36:15.423 --> 36:17.132
[MOANlNG]

36:19.969 --> 36:22.012
[GRUNTlNG]

36:24.223 --> 36:25.515
[MOANS]

36:25.683 --> 36:26.766
[LAUGHS]

36:26.934 --> 36:29.769
What? What is it?

36:31.022 --> 36:33.732
What is it?
You really are a virgin?

36:34.650 --> 36:38.904
Oh, no, no, no.
I'm teasing, I'm teasing.

36:39.071 --> 36:41.781
It was wonderful, really.
I could do it again.

36:41.949 --> 36:43.617
Let me try again.
It was wonderful.

36:44.285 --> 36:45.452
Really?
Yes.

36:47.163 --> 36:48.538
Hold me.

36:52.793 --> 36:54.794
[♪♪♪]

36:56.589 --> 36:58.173
MAN 1 :
And up.

36:59.258 --> 37:00.926
That's good. Pull it, your side.

37:01.093 --> 37:02.219
MAN 2:
There.

37:02.762 --> 37:04.471
MAN 1 :
Keep it tight.

37:04.722 --> 37:07.474
That's it, stretch it
so we can read it.

37:07.850 --> 37:11.144
Right, push it right firmly down
into the ground.

37:11.312 --> 37:14.731
[♪♪♪]

37:15.942 --> 37:17.484
MAN 1 :
We don't want it to blow over.

37:17.652 --> 37:19.653
[ROOSTER CROWS]

37:20.321 --> 37:21.905
That's good.

37:22.073 --> 37:23.490
[CHUCKLES]

37:24.242 --> 37:25.992
I'm sorry.

37:29.330 --> 37:30.622
Hi.

37:35.753 --> 37:37.003
[WHlSPERS lNDlSTlNCTLY]

37:37.171 --> 37:39.047
[LAUGHING]

37:42.176 --> 37:43.885
Oh...

37:45.429 --> 37:47.722
Why did you come here,
Masha?

37:49.767 --> 37:52.102
What do you mean?
What do you mean?

37:52.270 --> 37:54.813
You don't follow any
of the rules here.

37:56.357 --> 37:59.985
Because... Because
it's not about rules.

38:00.444 --> 38:01.820
Not for Tolstoy, anyway.

38:03.030 --> 38:04.823
Valentin Fedorovich.

38:04.991 --> 38:06.533
What is it?
Open the door.

38:06.701 --> 38:09.369
I'm currently indisposed.

38:09.537 --> 38:12.205
Yes, well,
Lev Nikolayevich
is downstairs.

38:12.373 --> 38:14.332
He wants to see you.

38:14.709 --> 38:18.545
VALENTIN:
Tell Lev Nikolayevich
I'll be down in a moment.

38:18.713 --> 38:22.841
Yes. And tell Maria Filipovna
we could use another hand
in the kitchen.

38:23.009 --> 38:26.303
If l see her, I will.
If you see her, yes.

38:26.470 --> 38:30.932
And if you're going to behave
like rabbits, you should
go live in the woods.

38:32.059 --> 38:33.101
[CHUCKLlNG]

38:33.269 --> 38:35.228
Shh!

38:35.688 --> 38:37.188
[SCOFFS]

38:37.356 --> 38:41.693
I'll go first. Give me
five minutes, yes?

38:42.820 --> 38:44.946
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

38:45.114 --> 38:48.575
Come on. That's a boy.

38:48.743 --> 38:50.410
That's my boy.

38:51.245 --> 38:53.038
You too, come on.

38:53.205 --> 38:56.875
You're wonderful, you're
just wonderful, wonderful.

38:58.210 --> 39:00.003
[LAUGHING]

39:00.171 --> 39:01.838
[♪♪♪]

39:02.006 --> 39:04.007
And you too, you too, son.

39:07.636 --> 39:10.764
Look at the love
in him. It's like...

39:11.932 --> 39:15.352
Jesus suffering
the children.

39:15.519 --> 39:17.103
All that.
I know, an old man's

39:17.271 --> 39:18.855
a very ugly thing. Yes.

39:20.316 --> 39:22.442
Hey, my boy! Hey!

39:22.610 --> 39:24.652
Come and kiss me.

39:27.239 --> 39:30.784
And who's this?
Maria Filipovna.

39:31.952 --> 39:34.371
Oh, you're both
looking so well.

39:34.538 --> 39:36.373
Life here obviously
agrees with you.

39:36.540 --> 39:37.624
[SNEEZES]

39:37.792 --> 39:41.961
God bless you, boy.
What are you nervous
about now?

39:42.129 --> 39:44.589
Sit down. Sit down.

39:45.007 --> 39:46.383
Oh, Masha, my dear.

39:51.013 --> 39:54.766
Valentin tells me
that you are the great
treasure of Telyatinki.

39:54.934 --> 39:58.478
He claims you're
a very gifted teacher.

39:59.939 --> 40:01.398
MASHA:
We're happy to have you with us.

40:01.565 --> 40:03.066
[INSECT BUZZING]

40:06.612 --> 40:08.071
What are you doing?

40:08.239 --> 40:11.324
What do you mean?
You just killed a living thing.

40:11.492 --> 40:13.243
[TOLSTOY & MASHA
CHUCKLlNG]

40:13.411 --> 40:15.495
Do you have
something to say?

40:16.539 --> 40:19.624
It's absurd, that's all.
What are you saying?

40:19.792 --> 40:22.836
I'm sorry, but it's a mosquito.
Forgive him. He can't help it.

40:23.003 --> 40:25.964
He's a much better
Tolstoyan than I am.

40:27.341 --> 40:29.801
That's not the message
we want to send.

40:31.846 --> 40:33.638
Please, have your seat.

40:36.559 --> 40:38.101
TOLSTOY:
Very well.

40:41.188 --> 40:43.189
Papa, from Mother:

40:43.357 --> 40:46.526
"Nerves dreadful. Stop.
Insomnia. Stop.

40:46.694 --> 40:49.195
Pulse 1 00. Stop.

40:49.822 --> 40:51.156
Please come home."

40:54.743 --> 40:57.078
[FOOTSTEPS]

41:00.833 --> 41:02.417
So...

41:02.918 --> 41:05.545
are you ill? Or what is it?

41:06.672 --> 41:10.133
Oh, l'm much better,
now you're here.

41:11.677 --> 41:15.221
It's no good, you know, all this.
You frightened everyone.

41:15.389 --> 41:19.309
Really? No, l don't
believe you. Not you.

41:20.603 --> 41:24.230
I'm your little bird.
You know the sounds l make.

41:24.398 --> 41:27.317
Then that was some
sort of love call, I suppose.

41:27.735 --> 41:29.736
Brought you back to me.

41:29.904 --> 41:31.404
[SIGHS]

41:32.239 --> 41:35.783
Why? Why, why,
why do you do it?

41:35.951 --> 41:39.412
We live in the country,
you insist on making it
an opera house!

41:39.580 --> 41:41.247
What's wrong with
a little peace now and then?

41:41.415 --> 41:43.166
Look at me!

41:43.334 --> 41:48.296
This is who l am.
This is what you married.

41:48.881 --> 41:52.008
We may be older,
maybe we're old,

41:52.760 --> 41:55.762
but I'm still your
little chicken.

41:55.930 --> 41:59.265
And you're still my big cock.
Oh, for pity's sake.

41:59.433 --> 42:01.226
[CHUCKLES]

42:01.393 --> 42:04.145
Let me make you crow.
Hm?

42:04.313 --> 42:07.023
[IMITATES ROOSTER
CROWlNG]

42:07.191 --> 42:09.943
Cock-a-doodle-doo.

42:10.110 --> 42:13.363
Oh, come on,
let me make you sing.

42:13.864 --> 42:15.740
Cock-a-doodle-doo!
No. No.

42:15.908 --> 42:17.325
No, no, no.

42:17.493 --> 42:18.952
[BOTH LAUGHING]

42:19.119 --> 42:21.621
Cock-a-doodle-doo.

42:21.789 --> 42:23.790
[BOTH LAUGHING]

42:24.959 --> 42:27.669
Cock-a-doodle-doo.

42:33.300 --> 42:34.884
[CROWS]

42:35.844 --> 42:37.845
[♪♪♪]

42:42.059 --> 42:44.227
Let me make you sing.

42:44.395 --> 42:46.396
[BOTH CLUCKING]

42:55.155 --> 42:57.991
Do you love me?
I do, l do. I do.

42:58.158 --> 43:01.828
I want you to love me.

43:03.998 --> 43:05.623
I do.

43:09.878 --> 43:11.337
[CROWS]

43:11.505 --> 43:12.714
[LAUGHS]

43:14.258 --> 43:15.883
[TOLSTOY CROWS]

43:16.051 --> 43:18.052
[BOTH LAUGHING]

43:20.848 --> 43:24.392
MAN: l must say you do look
beautiful in the firelight.

43:25.227 --> 43:27.854
WOMAN: You mean
I look beautiful in the dark.

43:30.399 --> 43:32.734
[PEOPLE CHATTERlNG]

43:35.279 --> 43:37.614
[INSTRUMENTS PLAYING]

43:41.201 --> 43:42.285
[MATCH STRlKES]

43:44.538 --> 43:46.080
Masha.

43:47.583 --> 43:49.626
You wouldn't look at me.

43:49.793 --> 43:51.502
Heh. I...

43:51.670 --> 43:53.671
It was difficult,
in front of the others...

43:53.839 --> 43:55.882
It wasn't difficult
in your bed

43:56.050 --> 43:58.176
when it was just
you and me in front of God.

43:58.344 --> 43:59.802
I'm not sure
I was aware of God.

43:59.970 --> 44:02.013
So l made you forget God?
No. Never.

44:02.181 --> 44:03.389
Yes. Yes.
Only for a moment.

44:03.557 --> 44:06.934
You forgot your rules
and you remembered love.

44:07.102 --> 44:10.271
You make it sound very simple.
It is simple.

44:10.439 --> 44:13.566
I mean, what we did
is what men and women do.

44:13.734 --> 44:16.486
It's what they have done,
it's what they'll continue doing.

44:17.905 --> 44:20.448
We touched each other.

44:20.616 --> 44:25.078
When we stayed close together,
something passed between us.

44:25.245 --> 44:26.746
Something real.

44:28.248 --> 44:30.625
And that's a betrayal
of what?

44:30.793 --> 44:31.876
Nothing.

44:33.545 --> 44:35.546
But you're afraid.

44:35.714 --> 44:37.924
All your ideas.

44:39.301 --> 44:42.303
[♪♪♪]

44:59.780 --> 45:01.989
Ah, she wants to question
you about the new will.

45:02.950 --> 45:05.076
[WHlSPERlNG]
But how does she
even know it exists?

45:05.244 --> 45:09.247
Well, she claims that
Lev Nikolayevich said
she could look at the draft.

45:10.958 --> 45:14.961
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Well, uh, he is obviously
not thinking clearly.

45:15.129 --> 45:17.630
And now we have to contend
with her petty grasping.

45:17.798 --> 45:19.215
It doesn't seem
that petty to me.

45:19.383 --> 45:21.134
I beg your pardon?

45:22.136 --> 45:23.636
Ah...

45:25.597 --> 45:29.392
He's her entire life.
The work, in her mind,
is theirs, together.

45:29.560 --> 45:30.935
And you're her advocate?

45:31.103 --> 45:33.521
You have been taken in
by her celebrity.

45:33.689 --> 45:35.231
I was worried about this.

45:35.399 --> 45:37.734
I'm simply talking
about their history.

45:37.901 --> 45:41.028
Nothing-- Nothing more.
We have to see her. Hm?

45:41.196 --> 45:42.780
Act as if nothing has happened.

45:42.948 --> 45:44.907
Nothing has
happened.

45:46.410 --> 45:51.080
Sofya Andreyevna.
At last, you honor us
with a visit.

45:51.248 --> 45:54.542
Well, l'm curious to see
how things are progressing
here at Telyatinki.

45:54.710 --> 45:56.169
Well...

45:57.045 --> 45:58.212
What is it?

45:58.380 --> 46:00.047
Ah, your mustache is...

46:00.215 --> 46:01.340
[CHUCKLES]

46:01.508 --> 46:03.509
No, it's just a problem
with the wax.

46:03.677 --> 46:04.719
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

46:05.387 --> 46:08.055
Vladimir Grigorevich,
let me come straight
to the point.

46:08.223 --> 46:09.849
I don't wish to
be your enemy.

46:10.017 --> 46:13.770
On the contrary,
I am delighted that my
husband has found a friend

46:13.937 --> 46:17.523
who understands
and shares his ideals.

46:17.691 --> 46:20.985
I just want
what's reasonable.

46:21.153 --> 46:24.781
I want an opportunity
to evaluate the new will.

46:26.033 --> 46:28.367
If you agree, then I'm sure
we can be friends.

46:28.535 --> 46:33.664
You are very kind,
Sofya Andreyevna,
but I can't help you.

46:33.832 --> 46:37.543
Not without specific
instructions from
your husband.

46:40.547 --> 46:42.548
Oh, he has agreed.
Hasn't he, Valentin?

46:42.716 --> 46:46.928
No witness you produce
can change my position,
I'm afraid.

46:47.095 --> 46:48.221
But I will, of course,

46:48.388 --> 46:51.224
speak to Lev Nikolayevich
at the first opportunity.

46:51.391 --> 46:53.893
[♪♪♪]

46:54.895 --> 46:56.813
Very well.

46:56.980 --> 46:59.398
I want us to be
friends too, Sofya.

46:59.566 --> 47:04.070
Lev Nikolayevich is
the most valuable thing
in the world, to both of us.

47:04.238 --> 47:06.072
We should endeavor
to set things right
between us.

47:06.240 --> 47:09.242
Give him peace.
Let him work.

47:10.786 --> 47:11.828
Yes.
Mm.

47:19.586 --> 47:23.548
Valentin Fedorovich,
would you accompany me
to the house, please?

47:23.715 --> 47:25.049
I...

47:26.760 --> 47:29.762
Uh, I'll accompany the,
ahem, countess back
to the house

47:29.930 --> 47:32.765
and be back in time
for supper.

47:34.226 --> 47:36.185
SERGEYENKO:
Masha will be overjoyed.

47:41.859 --> 47:44.360
[♪♪♪]

47:45.612 --> 47:49.031
SOFYA: Valentin Fedorovich,
you've been keeping
something from me.

47:49.199 --> 47:50.783
Have l?

47:51.451 --> 47:54.120
You can tell me anything,
Valentin.

47:54.955 --> 47:56.873
I love a romance.

47:57.040 --> 47:58.332
[LAUGHS]

47:58.500 --> 48:00.501
That's-- lt's nothing.
Really, it's nothing.

48:00.669 --> 48:02.628
A young woman
in your life is nothing?

48:02.796 --> 48:04.630
Masha is a friend.

48:05.007 --> 48:09.218
A lover?
A very-- A very good friend.

48:09.636 --> 48:11.929
See, you forget that
I'm an experienced reader,

48:12.097 --> 48:16.267
so l can read your face,
every letter.

48:16.435 --> 48:18.895
It's beautifully clear.

48:19.062 --> 48:20.104
Really?

48:21.440 --> 48:23.107
Do you love her?

48:25.193 --> 48:27.945
I think perhaps l do.
Yes.

48:32.993 --> 48:34.368
It's not something
they'd understand,

48:34.536 --> 48:36.579
these so-called disciples
of my husband's.

48:36.747 --> 48:39.707
They've never understood
a word he's ever written.

48:43.629 --> 48:45.963
What do they
know about love?

49:07.611 --> 49:11.197
MAN: Let's try to be as efficient
as possible, get the job done,
and get back.

49:23.710 --> 49:24.752
Whoa!

49:24.920 --> 49:31.008
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

49:31.176 --> 49:33.177
Did I scare you? Are you all right?
Fine.

49:33.345 --> 49:35.388
I'm sorry.

49:35.555 --> 49:36.973
I got back as soon
as l could.

49:38.892 --> 49:41.686
It was a strange day.
Lev Nikolayevich is...

49:41.853 --> 49:46.941
I love to listen to him talk,
but today l could barely
concentrate.

49:48.193 --> 49:49.694
All...

49:49.861 --> 49:52.154
All I could think about
was you.

49:53.490 --> 49:56.784
I think I've confused you.
No.

49:56.952 --> 49:59.078
I think I've confused us both.
No.

49:59.746 --> 50:02.915
I... I was stupid.

50:04.126 --> 50:06.585
I was afraid,
but I'm not afraid anymore.

50:06.753 --> 50:08.379
Whoa.
What are you...?

50:12.050 --> 50:13.592
Masha.

50:15.387 --> 50:17.555
I love you, Masha.

50:25.897 --> 50:26.939
[SIGHS]

50:41.246 --> 50:42.788
Here.

50:49.755 --> 50:51.130
Masha.

50:54.176 --> 50:56.510
Masha! I have...

50:58.638 --> 51:00.639
In my heart,

51:01.099 --> 51:05.352
I have committed the act
of copulation many times!

51:11.735 --> 51:14.487
Please know it was never
like it was with you.

51:14.654 --> 51:16.989
[♪♪♪]

51:21.369 --> 51:23.162
I'll wait for you, then.

51:23.663 --> 51:25.081
You will?

51:26.500 --> 51:27.625
Give me this.

51:27.793 --> 51:29.043
[MASHA LAUGHlNG]

51:29.211 --> 51:32.088
VALENTIN: What?
What are you laughing at?

51:33.298 --> 51:34.840
It's a problem with the wax.

51:35.008 --> 51:37.009
[BOTH LAUGHING]

51:40.180 --> 51:42.973
I think I look just like him.

51:46.645 --> 51:48.145
You're happy.

51:48.313 --> 51:49.522
Well, of course I am.

51:50.649 --> 51:54.485
Love and be loved.
That's the only reality
there is in the world.

51:55.070 --> 51:56.987
He said that?

51:57.906 --> 52:00.866
Yes, Tolstoy said it,
but I'm saying it.

52:03.036 --> 52:06.038
I'm saying it, Masha,
because you make me know it.

52:06.373 --> 52:09.708
I look into your eyes
and l can see the future.

52:11.920 --> 52:14.964
I think you're the bravest
person l've ever met.

52:16.758 --> 52:18.843
You amaze me.

52:19.845 --> 52:22.847
You believe more
than I know how to.

52:25.016 --> 52:26.684
I love you.

52:31.731 --> 52:34.024
You're pure, Valya.

52:38.446 --> 52:40.990
You're what
I came here to find.

52:55.755 --> 52:56.922
[SNIFFS]

52:58.341 --> 53:01.010
Ivan, who's wearing
that awful perfume?

53:01.178 --> 53:03.512
[FOOTSTEPS]

53:07.225 --> 53:10.853
CHERTKOV:
I understand this is difficult.
It is a delicate situation.

53:11.021 --> 53:12.771
This way.

53:12.939 --> 53:17.026
This must be discussed now.
It cannot wait any longer.

53:17.903 --> 53:19.486
SASHA:
Whatever happens,
Mother mustn't find out.

53:19.654 --> 53:20.696
CHERTKOV:
Shh.

53:21.698 --> 53:25.326
I hate to say it, but the
countess has become
more and more dangerous.

53:25.493 --> 53:29.413
Oh, not dangerous.
She's concerned for
the welfare of the family.

53:29.581 --> 53:32.458
And we're concerned
with the welfare of mankind.

53:32.626 --> 53:35.002
[♪♪♪]

53:38.131 --> 53:39.465
CHERTKOV:
You've been more
than reasonable.

53:39.633 --> 53:41.050
TOLSTOY:
Have l?

53:41.218 --> 53:42.760
Of course you have.

53:42.928 --> 53:45.262
She already controls
the income from your property.

53:45.430 --> 53:48.349
Please, listen to him,
Papa. He has our best
interests at heart.

53:48.516 --> 53:51.727
We are speaking
only of the rights to
your words, your ideas.

53:51.895 --> 53:53.854
With all love and respect,

53:54.022 --> 53:57.650
the countess is too interested
in making a profit from your work.

54:03.615 --> 54:07.243
TOLSTOY:
She's my wife. She's part of me.
We've been together all these years.

54:07.410 --> 54:10.829
But you're more than
a husband and father.
She must understand that.

54:10.997 --> 54:13.540
The best interests of the people
are one with your own.

54:13.708 --> 54:14.750
You belong to them.

54:14.918 --> 54:17.878
TOLSTOY: She won't.
She'll never understand.

54:19.673 --> 54:21.131
WOMAN:
What is she doing?

54:21.299 --> 54:23.717
CHERTKOV:
She's unstable.
I wonder if she isn't ill.

54:23.885 --> 54:24.927
It's sadly more
than probable.

54:25.095 --> 54:27.846
I know it's hard for you, Papa,
but you must be realistic.

54:28.014 --> 54:30.182
CHERTKOV:
Her behavior is extremely alarming.

54:31.268 --> 54:35.020
Do you truly think that
she is fit to control the
final disposition of this will?

54:35.188 --> 54:36.522
TOLSTOY:
Well, l don't-- l don't--

54:36.690 --> 54:37.856
SOFYA:
How dare-- Aah!

54:39.276 --> 54:41.527
TOLSTOY: God!
Oh, God.

54:42.153 --> 54:44.321
What are you doing?

54:44.489 --> 54:48.534
You're all plotting against me,
in my own house too!

54:49.202 --> 54:51.996
I bear you 1 3 children.

54:52.163 --> 54:55.582
How can you
betray me like this?

54:56.042 --> 54:58.460
Somebody, help me up.

55:01.840 --> 55:04.300
Go ahead. Go ahead.

55:05.010 --> 55:07.386
Why don't you give everything
we've got to him?

55:07.554 --> 55:08.721
Your fat little catamite!

55:08.888 --> 55:13.017
"What will it be,
my dearest darling,
my Vladimir Grigorevich?

55:13.184 --> 55:16.687
My wife's heart on a platter?
Her kidneys, with salt?

55:16.855 --> 55:19.440
But of course, my dear Chertkov.
Whatever pleases you.

55:19.607 --> 55:20.733
The china, the estate,

55:20.900 --> 55:23.360
permanent copyright
on anything I've ever written?

55:23.528 --> 55:26.405
Oh, anything for you,
my love."

55:26.573 --> 55:27.656
[SCRIBBLING]

55:27.824 --> 55:29.074
[GASPS]

55:32.620 --> 55:34.163
Give that to me.
No.

55:34.331 --> 55:36.832
Give it to me, you little weasel!
Sofya!

55:37.000 --> 55:39.043
Give it to me! Give it to me!
DUSHAN: Sofya.

55:40.170 --> 55:41.253
Now...
Can I have--?

55:41.421 --> 55:43.672
Can I not have some...?

55:43.840 --> 55:48.385
Can I not have some...?
You'll kill him, Mama.

55:48.553 --> 55:52.431
Well, that's what you want,
isn't it? You want him to die!

55:52.849 --> 55:54.266
Lev.

55:57.437 --> 56:00.606
DUSHAN:
It's all right, it's all right.
Let's get him out of here.

56:09.074 --> 56:11.575
You don't deceive me
for one moment.

56:11.743 --> 56:14.828
I know exactly
what you're doing.

56:18.958 --> 56:20.793
I want to see the will.

56:21.753 --> 56:25.464
It is my right as his wife
in the sight of God.

56:25.632 --> 56:27.800
What are you afraid of?

56:27.967 --> 56:29.468
You.

56:30.011 --> 56:31.553
I'm afraid of you.

56:33.973 --> 56:35.641
The press are
bloodthirsty, Sofya.

56:35.809 --> 56:38.811
Had I wished,
I could have demolished you.

56:38.978 --> 56:40.020
You make it easy.

56:40.188 --> 56:42.606
Then tell them anything
you want. Go ahead. Ruin us!

56:42.774 --> 56:45.984
I have too much respect
for Lev Nikolayevich!

56:46.152 --> 56:47.403
You're lucky!

56:47.570 --> 56:49.988
Why can't my husband
see you for what you are?

56:50.156 --> 56:55.035
If l had a wife like you,
I would've blown my brains out!

56:55.412 --> 56:58.163
Or gone to America.

56:59.582 --> 57:00.874
[DOOR SLAMS]

57:05.588 --> 57:07.506
[SOBBING]

57:27.986 --> 57:31.947
[PUCCINI'S "UN BEL DI,
VEDREMO" PLAYlNG]

57:41.916 --> 57:44.042
I hope you're feeling better.

57:44.210 --> 57:45.294
Mm.

57:49.382 --> 57:51.341
Do you like the opera?

57:51.885 --> 57:53.385
Yes.

57:53.553 --> 57:55.053
[CHUCKLES]

57:58.808 --> 58:02.311
I'm very sorry
about everything.

58:05.023 --> 58:06.523
[WHlMPERS]

58:08.151 --> 58:10.694
This aria is so beautiful.

58:11.571 --> 58:15.491
It's about a woman
who's been abandoned
by the man she loves.

58:15.658 --> 58:18.076
Everyone finds that
very moving...

58:19.245 --> 58:21.079
in the opera.

58:25.793 --> 58:27.503
[DOOR OPENS]

58:32.509 --> 58:35.594
Our life together
has become intolerable.

58:36.262 --> 58:37.387
SOFYA:
Sit down, Valentin.

58:37.805 --> 58:39.056
Really, l'm expected
at Telyatinki.

58:39.224 --> 58:41.016
No, no, no, please.
Come, enjoy your dinner.

58:41.184 --> 58:44.770
We've just had a disagreement,
like all married couples.

58:45.688 --> 58:49.274
Despite good cause for it,
I have never stopped loving you.

58:49.442 --> 58:51.151
Of course.

58:51.319 --> 58:53.111
But God knows
you don't make it easy.

58:53.279 --> 58:54.279
SOFYA:
Why should it be easy?

58:54.447 --> 58:56.740
I am the work of your life,
you're the work of mine.

58:56.908 --> 58:59.117
That's what love is.

59:00.245 --> 59:01.620
I should go.
No, sit down.

59:03.248 --> 59:07.668
Oh, so that's what love is?
Eh?

59:08.294 --> 59:09.378
Does that surprise you, boy?

59:09.546 --> 59:10.963
I thought it might be
a touch quieter, but--

59:11.130 --> 59:12.256
[SNEEZES]

59:12.423 --> 59:13.757
God bless you.
Bless you.

59:13.925 --> 59:16.009
He's right, though.

59:17.053 --> 59:20.138
If we can't live a decent, quiet life,

59:20.306 --> 59:24.935
if l can't work and find some
peace, then I shall go away.

59:25.103 --> 59:28.355
Go?
Not to Chertkov, but I shall go.

59:28.523 --> 59:31.775
Go where?
Dushan says you're killing me!

59:33.820 --> 59:36.113
Then go!
Go anywhere you please!

59:37.323 --> 59:39.741
Go anywhere you please!

59:40.493 --> 59:42.744
I hate you!

59:44.038 --> 59:45.497
I hate what you've become!

59:46.499 --> 59:49.126
VALENTIN: Countess.
Go. No.

59:49.294 --> 59:50.335
Dushan!

59:51.421 --> 59:54.298
Oh, God.
Countess?

59:54.799 --> 59:57.509
Countess! Is she all right?

59:57.677 --> 59:59.052
Is she all right?

59:59.220 --> 01:00:03.765
Sofya. Sofya,
are you all right?
Open your eyes.

01:00:03.933 --> 01:00:05.142
Open your eyes.

01:00:06.769 --> 01:00:08.854
Oh! Oh, my back!

01:00:09.022 --> 01:00:10.272
Oh, my-- Oh!

01:00:10.732 --> 01:00:12.024
Oh, my back.

01:00:13.443 --> 01:00:15.110
DUSHAN:
You're lying on a fork.

01:00:18.072 --> 01:00:20.532
Sit up and you'll
improve markedly.

01:00:21.200 --> 01:00:23.785
If you'll be good enough
to take her upstairs.

01:00:23.953 --> 01:00:26.538
Come along, countess,
come with me.

01:00:26.873 --> 01:00:29.875
[COUGHlNG]

01:00:35.381 --> 01:00:36.632
[GROANS]

01:00:41.220 --> 01:00:42.429
[FOOTSTEPS]

01:00:46.559 --> 01:00:47.726
Masha.

01:01:00.823 --> 01:01:02.240
I'm sorry.

01:01:05.203 --> 01:01:06.495
It was terrible there today.

01:01:07.914 --> 01:01:11.583
They loved each other so much,
I'm sure of it, l'm sure they do,

01:01:11.751 --> 01:01:15.003
but you see what it becomes,
and you just wish that you could...

01:01:15.922 --> 01:01:17.255
[SIGHS]

01:01:19.592 --> 01:01:21.301
Is something
the matter?

01:01:22.011 --> 01:01:23.387
Masha?

01:01:26.391 --> 01:01:29.559
I'm-- I'm going back
to Moscow.

01:01:30.311 --> 01:01:31.353
What?

01:01:31.521 --> 01:01:34.690
Chertkov spoke with me
this afternoon.

01:01:34.857 --> 01:01:37.859
He said l could
be more useful there.

01:01:38.027 --> 01:01:40.070
Which means...
Means he's punishing us.

01:01:40.238 --> 01:01:42.698
He's punishing me.

01:01:42.865 --> 01:01:45.534
He's punishing me
for befriending
Sofya Andreyevna.

01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:46.785
This is Chertkov.

01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:49.037
We've both
disappointed him,
but I don't care.

01:01:49.205 --> 01:01:51.206
I don't care either,
but you can't leave.

01:01:51.374 --> 01:01:54.292
I'm going to talk to him.
I'm going to make him
make you stay.

01:01:54.460 --> 01:01:57.838
No. I want to go.
Yes. What?

01:01:58.548 --> 01:02:00.549
I'm leaving the movement.

01:02:02.343 --> 01:02:03.844
[CHUCKLES]

01:02:04.262 --> 01:02:05.554
[STAMMERS]

01:02:06.472 --> 01:02:08.515
Sit down, sit down.

01:02:10.101 --> 01:02:11.893
You can't leave Tolstoy.
I'm not.

01:02:12.061 --> 01:02:14.479
You can't leave.
No, I'm not.

01:02:16.149 --> 01:02:18.400
When I read his confession,
it moved me, Valya.

01:02:18.568 --> 01:02:19.609
Yes.

01:02:19.777 --> 01:02:21.903
When he was searching
for freedom.

01:02:22.071 --> 01:02:25.240
Freedom from anger,
freedom from attachment,

01:02:25.408 --> 01:02:28.994
freedom from all the superstition
and the nonsense of the Church.

01:02:29.162 --> 01:02:32.164
I mean, it moved me
so much.

01:02:32.331 --> 01:02:34.666
And that's what I thought
it would be about.

01:02:34.834 --> 01:02:37.127
I mean, isn't that
what it's about?

01:02:37.378 --> 01:02:39.546
Freedom and love?

01:02:41.841 --> 01:02:44.384
They mix it all up.

01:02:44.969 --> 01:02:46.219
[SCOFFS]

01:02:50.224 --> 01:02:51.975
Come with me.

01:02:54.729 --> 01:02:56.188
Please?

01:03:05.198 --> 01:03:07.532
[♪♪♪]

01:03:11.287 --> 01:03:12.329
I can't.

01:03:23.591 --> 01:03:26.968
I'm going to my room.
Wait.

01:03:28.429 --> 01:03:29.930
Masha.

01:03:38.231 --> 01:03:41.316
Masha, please. I can't.

01:03:42.109 --> 01:03:43.568
I need you.

01:03:49.075 --> 01:03:50.659
I know you do.

01:03:52.954 --> 01:03:54.913
I know.

01:04:07.009 --> 01:04:10.303
SOFYA:
A-Y . A-Y .

01:04:11.597 --> 01:04:13.849
A-Y .

01:04:15.810 --> 01:04:18.270
What was it?
I don't remember.

01:04:19.605 --> 01:04:23.525
Was it your...?
No, no, no.

01:04:23.693 --> 01:04:25.902
You rest now.

01:04:27.446 --> 01:04:28.989
You rest.

01:04:30.324 --> 01:04:32.409
[MOANlNG]

01:04:44.380 --> 01:04:46.381
[♪♪♪]

01:05:03.816 --> 01:05:05.984
CHERTKOV:
Is everything in order?

01:05:06.152 --> 01:05:08.069
[PEOPLE SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:05:22.335 --> 01:05:24.169
CHERTKOV:
Good afternoon,
Lev Nikolayevich.

01:05:24.337 --> 01:05:25.670
Is it?

01:05:41.270 --> 01:05:43.772
Remember that this will ensure

01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:46.900
that your complete works
will live in the public domain.

01:05:47.068 --> 01:05:48.610
Monumentous.

01:05:48.778 --> 01:05:52.822
Your works are the birthright
of the Russian people.

01:05:52.990 --> 01:05:57.202
And now they will
possess them forever.

01:05:59.205 --> 01:06:00.705
Yes?

01:06:01.415 --> 01:06:03.249
I need a pen.

01:06:03.584 --> 01:06:06.461
Oh. Of course, of course.

01:06:07.546 --> 01:06:09.714
I, uh...
What?

01:06:14.470 --> 01:06:15.887
I don't seem
to have a pen.

01:06:16.055 --> 01:06:18.348
You're a secretary.
How can you not have a pen?

01:06:18.516 --> 01:06:21.267
He's a secretary too.
Ask him.

01:06:22.061 --> 01:06:25.188
Valentin Fedorovich,
do you have a pen?

01:06:25.356 --> 01:06:26.856
I...

01:06:30.111 --> 01:06:32.779
[♪♪♪]

01:06:35.241 --> 01:06:36.658
Yes.

01:06:37.827 --> 01:06:39.744
Yes, l have a pen.

01:06:54.301 --> 01:06:56.094
Are you all right?

01:06:58.097 --> 01:06:59.597
I'm a conspirator.

01:07:00.474 --> 01:07:01.725
Nothing more.

01:07:01.892 --> 01:07:03.435
[CHUCKLES]

01:07:10.443 --> 01:07:12.444
[TYPEWRlTER CLACKING]

01:07:36.510 --> 01:07:38.678
VALENTIN:
Lev Nikolayevich.

01:07:38.846 --> 01:07:41.765
May I ask you a question
that has nothing to do
with the work?

01:07:41.932 --> 01:07:43.391
Of course, my dear.

01:07:44.351 --> 01:07:46.561
Do you love your wife?

01:07:49.190 --> 01:07:51.649
You see, when l was
courting Sofya,

01:07:51.817 --> 01:07:55.111
she was so young
and so pure

01:07:55.821 --> 01:07:58.907
it just seemed impossible
that I could ever have her.

01:07:59.325 --> 01:08:02.577
I didn't want to tell her
how I felt, and yet...

01:08:03.037 --> 01:08:05.789
I wanted to tell her
nothing else.

01:08:06.248 --> 01:08:08.083
So l wrote down
a string of letters

01:08:08.250 --> 01:08:10.835
and asked her
if she would decipher them.

01:08:11.003 --> 01:08:15.006
At first, she was completely
confused and thought it was
some sort of game or something.

01:08:15.174 --> 01:08:17.300
So l gave her a clue.
One clue.

01:08:18.219 --> 01:08:22.930
"The first two Y's," I said,
"stand for 'your youth,"'

01:08:23.099 --> 01:08:24.849
and that was all l said.

01:08:25.017 --> 01:08:26.142
And then...

01:08:27.019 --> 01:08:29.687
the most miraculous thing
happened.

01:08:30.648 --> 01:08:33.358
She simply spoke
the phrase:

01:08:34.568 --> 01:08:38.863
"Your youth and your desire
for happiness

01:08:39.031 --> 01:08:41.533
cruelly remind me of my age

01:08:41.700 --> 01:08:45.203
and the impossibility
of happiness for me."

01:08:46.538 --> 01:08:49.124
The entire phrase, my phrase.

01:08:49.707 --> 01:08:52.210
As if she'd read my mind.

01:08:53.754 --> 01:08:57.298
In that moment, we both knew
we would always be together.

01:08:58.466 --> 01:09:01.553
And for the first few years,
we were

01:09:01.886 --> 01:09:03.595
incredibly,

01:09:04.055 --> 01:09:06.140
terrifyingly...

01:09:08.769 --> 01:09:10.310
happy.

01:09:11.272 --> 01:09:13.189
[♪♪♪]

01:09:17.903 --> 01:09:19.696
And now this.

01:09:19.904 --> 01:09:22.407
[♪♪♪]

01:09:37.590 --> 01:09:38.881
VALENTIN:
I'm leaving Telyatinki.

01:09:39.758 --> 01:09:40.841
Really?

01:09:41.010 --> 01:09:43.094
Yes. l'm going to Moscow.

01:09:43.761 --> 01:09:45.805
She's leading you around
by the nose, my boy.

01:09:45.973 --> 01:09:49.267
Look, you say that
the movement is about love.

01:09:49.435 --> 01:09:52.520
And it is. The love
that he teaches us.

01:09:52.688 --> 01:09:55.440
The love that binds
all mankind together.

01:09:55.608 --> 01:09:57.442
I've never met mankind.

01:09:57.610 --> 01:10:01.321
I've only ever met men or women.
Imperfect men, imperfect women.

01:10:01.488 --> 01:10:04.115
Yes. But Lev Nikolayevich
also teaches us

01:10:04.283 --> 01:10:08.620
that love cannot
be weak-minded.
It cannot be stupid.

01:10:09.872 --> 01:10:11.289
[SCOFFS]

01:10:12.541 --> 01:10:15.710
Go. We will miss you.

01:10:17.129 --> 01:10:19.631
Our naive sentimentalist.

01:10:21.800 --> 01:10:23.635
MAN:
Keep clear.

01:10:25.471 --> 01:10:27.430
BOY:
Give it to me.

01:10:30.935 --> 01:10:32.852
[SNORING]

01:10:36.065 --> 01:10:38.107
SOFYA: Leovochka?
Hm?

01:10:38.275 --> 01:10:40.193
[FOOTSTEPS]

01:10:44.323 --> 01:10:48.159
Kashnikov wants to buy
the rights to your work
after your death.

01:10:48.327 --> 01:10:50.703
Oh, then I shall try and die
as soon as is convenient.

01:10:50.871 --> 01:10:53.122
Oh, come on, don't be silly.
Come, look.

01:10:53.290 --> 01:10:57.168
Look, he has offered
1 million rubles.

01:10:59.171 --> 01:11:01.005
How can you not be pleased?

01:11:01.173 --> 01:11:03.091
I don't write for publishers,
I write for people.

01:11:03.259 --> 01:11:04.509
Well, where are
you going?

01:11:04.677 --> 01:11:07.470
Valentin is in the library.
He wants to see me.

01:11:07.638 --> 01:11:11.266
Fine! Fine, go ahead
and let your wretched
family starve.

01:11:11.850 --> 01:11:15.019
I don't see anyone starving
in this house.

01:11:15.187 --> 01:11:16.854
On the contrary,

01:11:17.022 --> 01:11:19.524
our privilege revolts me.

01:11:19.817 --> 01:11:21.526
Well, you're the first
to the trough!

01:11:23.904 --> 01:11:25.947
Always have been.

01:11:43.048 --> 01:11:45.049
[♪♪♪]

01:12:04.987 --> 01:12:07.322
TOLSTOY:
Now, what is it, my boy?

01:12:07.740 --> 01:12:09.699
You look unhappy.

01:12:11.160 --> 01:12:13.119
What do you
want to tell me?

01:12:13.579 --> 01:12:17.582
[GUNSHOT]

01:12:23.255 --> 01:12:24.797
TOLSTOY:
Sofya!

01:12:25.466 --> 01:12:27.091
Sofya!

01:12:32.431 --> 01:12:34.265
What are you doing?

01:12:34.933 --> 01:12:38.061
How could you
do this to me?

01:12:38.979 --> 01:12:40.188
TOLSTOY:
You're not well.

01:12:40.356 --> 01:12:44.400
You-- You just hurt me
again and again.

01:12:44.568 --> 01:12:48.363
You tear pieces off me
until there's nothing left.

01:12:50.366 --> 01:12:53.368
I don't know who I am anymore.

01:12:56.705 --> 01:12:59.123
I read your diary.

01:13:00.292 --> 01:13:02.460
I know what
you've done.

01:13:03.587 --> 01:13:05.421
TOLSTOY:
You behave like this,
I have no choice.

01:13:07.800 --> 01:13:09.300
Now give me the gun.
No!

01:13:09.468 --> 01:13:12.095
Please, countess.
Give me the gun, please.

01:13:14.723 --> 01:13:16.265
[GUN CLATTERS]

01:13:18.060 --> 01:13:19.811
[SOFYA SOBBlNG]

01:13:25.150 --> 01:13:27.652
[♪♪♪]

01:13:56.974 --> 01:13:59.517
I'd like you to
stay here tonight.

01:14:02.563 --> 01:14:03.604
Yes, of course.

01:14:28.589 --> 01:14:29.714
SASHA [WHISPERING]:
Valentin.

01:14:29.882 --> 01:14:31.007
Get up.
VALENTIN: What?

01:14:31.175 --> 01:14:32.925
He's leaving.

01:14:37.097 --> 01:14:38.890
Shh!

01:14:43.770 --> 01:14:46.481
Pack essentials only.

01:14:47.149 --> 01:14:50.568
Nothing that isn't
absolutely necessary.

01:14:50.736 --> 01:14:52.320
Please, we must hurry.

01:14:52.488 --> 01:14:54.197
Where will you go?
SASHA: Your coat, Papa.

01:14:54.364 --> 01:14:55.907
We don't need a plan,
we just go.

01:14:56.074 --> 01:14:59.035
A lantern, I think.
It's very dark tonight.

01:14:59.203 --> 01:15:01.913
And the apparatus
for giving an enema.

01:15:10.422 --> 01:15:12.381
Everything's ready.

01:15:16.637 --> 01:15:17.762
[DUSHAN GRUNTS]

01:15:17.930 --> 01:15:19.764
VALENTIN:
Dushan, you all right?

01:15:20.140 --> 01:15:21.641
SASHA:
Please, go steady.

01:15:21.808 --> 01:15:23.392
VALENTIN:
You all right?

01:15:23.560 --> 01:15:25.019
Papa?

01:15:28.815 --> 01:15:30.650
He's changed
his mind.

01:15:30.817 --> 01:15:32.735
He's going back
to the house.

01:16:04.476 --> 01:16:06.811
Do you want
to go back?

01:16:08.981 --> 01:16:10.565
No.

01:16:12.276 --> 01:16:16.195
This life is behind me now.

01:16:16.363 --> 01:16:18.698
[♪♪♪]

01:16:31.837 --> 01:16:33.921
Help me up.
Yes, of course.

01:16:44.057 --> 01:16:46.100
Give this to Sofya.

01:16:46.268 --> 01:16:47.893
Yes.

01:16:53.191 --> 01:16:55.735
SASHA:
Be well, be well.

01:16:55.902 --> 01:16:57.695
[SOBBING]

01:17:04.870 --> 01:17:07.538
Don't cry, don't cry.

01:17:07.998 --> 01:17:10.041
I'll send for you when I can.

01:17:23.347 --> 01:17:25.056
DUSHAN:
Drive on.

01:17:48.914 --> 01:17:50.706
He's gone.

01:17:51.750 --> 01:17:54.251
For good?
I think so, yes.

01:17:56.880 --> 01:18:00.174
Oh, Sasha, darling,
I know you know
where your father is.

01:18:00.342 --> 01:18:03.344
So, darling, please,
this is not a time to
play games, please?

01:18:03.512 --> 01:18:07.765
Countess, I have this for you.

01:18:15.273 --> 01:18:16.691
[♪♪♪]

01:18:16.858 --> 01:18:21.946
TOLSTOY:
My position in the house
has become intolerable.

01:18:22.114 --> 01:18:26.659
What l'm doing now is what
people have commonly done,

01:18:27.285 --> 01:18:29.161
leave their worldly life behind

01:18:29.329 --> 01:18:34.250
to spend their last days
in peace and solitude.

01:18:35.001 --> 01:18:36.627
[SOFYA SCREAMS]

01:18:38.338 --> 01:18:39.588
[SOFYA SOBS]

01:18:39.756 --> 01:18:41.924
The pond.

01:18:43.468 --> 01:18:45.469
SASHA: Mama!
VALENTIN: Countess!

01:18:45.637 --> 01:18:46.721
Please, Mama!

01:18:46.888 --> 01:18:49.557
Please understand this
and don't come after me,

01:18:49.725 --> 01:18:51.976
even if you find out where I am.

01:18:52.477 --> 01:18:55.146
Your coming would only
make our position worse

01:18:55.313 --> 01:18:57.565
and would not alter my decision.

01:18:57.733 --> 01:18:59.608
SASHA:
Mother!

01:19:01.236 --> 01:19:04.989
I beg you to forgive me
for everything l've done to you,

01:19:05.157 --> 01:19:07.658
just as l forgive you
with all my soul

01:19:08.493 --> 01:19:10.995
for everything you've done to me.

01:19:11.163 --> 01:19:13.497
[♪♪♪]

01:19:19.796 --> 01:19:20.921
VALENTIN:
Countess!

01:19:27.304 --> 01:19:32.141
Mama!

01:19:33.852 --> 01:19:36.687
Mama!
I have her!

01:19:39.524 --> 01:19:44.820
Here! Here! Take her! Take her.
Mama!

01:19:49.785 --> 01:19:53.871
SASHA:
Ivan, Ivan, go to the house.
Get a doctor, quickly, quickly!

01:19:54.706 --> 01:19:57.917
Turn her.
Turn her over, come on.

01:20:00.045 --> 01:20:02.963
[COUGHlNG]

01:20:03.215 --> 01:20:05.382
Oh, God. Thank God.

01:20:20.732 --> 01:20:25.236
Ivan, go to the station.
Find out which train he took.

01:20:25.904 --> 01:20:27.321
For God's sake.

01:20:28.365 --> 01:20:31.283
Come, come, come.
Let's get you to bed.

01:20:31.451 --> 01:20:34.703
Ready and up. There we...
IVAN: Let's go, there.

01:20:38.583 --> 01:20:40.376
SASHA:
Thank you.

01:20:48.718 --> 01:20:50.135
[DOOR OPENS]

01:21:02.357 --> 01:21:05.234
Here, tea.

01:21:06.403 --> 01:21:08.612
She's exhausted
herself.

01:21:08.780 --> 01:21:10.948
She slept for
nearly four hours.

01:21:11.116 --> 01:21:15.119
Well, l'm glad she can sleep.
The pain subsides a little.

01:21:15.287 --> 01:21:18.122
The noise subsides
a little.

01:21:18.540 --> 01:21:20.124
[BOTH LAUGHING]

01:21:20.375 --> 01:21:21.792
[KNOCKlNG ON DOOR]

01:21:21.960 --> 01:21:23.460
Come in.

01:21:24.337 --> 01:21:27.047
A message, miss.
For me?

01:21:27.799 --> 01:21:29.133
From your father.

01:21:29.926 --> 01:21:32.136
[♪♪♪]

01:21:32.304 --> 01:21:36.765
TOLSTOY:
My darling Sasha, l have stopped
to rest at Shamardino.

01:21:36.933 --> 01:21:39.810
I'll wait for you to join me here.

01:21:39.978 --> 01:21:43.480
Please ask Valentin to stay
and look after your mother.

01:21:43.648 --> 01:21:47.985
When you arrive, we'll continue
the journey south together.

01:21:48.153 --> 01:21:49.445
Your loving father.

01:22:05.962 --> 01:22:07.671
They've all gone.

01:22:08.673 --> 01:22:10.341
I'm here.

01:22:13.261 --> 01:22:14.803
Oh...

01:22:15.138 --> 01:22:19.475
You're writing to your girl.
Oh, how lovely.

01:22:19.643 --> 01:22:22.144
I'm not sure she is my girl.

01:22:22.437 --> 01:22:24.521
But you believe
you'll see her again.

01:22:24.689 --> 01:22:26.815
I very much hope so.
Yes.

01:22:26.983 --> 01:22:28.359
Yes.

01:22:29.778 --> 01:22:32.780
I know you know
where he is, Valentin.

01:22:34.324 --> 01:22:38.953
Sofya Andreyevna--
I won't ask you to betray his trust.

01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:42.539
I just need you
to go to him. I do.

01:22:42.707 --> 01:22:45.542
I have to see him.
I have to talk to him.

01:22:45.710 --> 01:22:49.380
I won't make a scene.
You can promise him that. I--

01:22:51.716 --> 01:22:54.009
I just want to see him.

01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:02.101
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLARlNG]

01:23:05.563 --> 01:23:09.233
DUSHAN:
"Tolstoy abandons home,
whereabouts unknown."

01:23:09.693 --> 01:23:12.861
"The sage of Yasnaya Polyana
takes flight."

01:23:13.029 --> 01:23:14.947
WOMAN [WHlSPERS]:
That's Tolstoy.

01:23:15.991 --> 01:23:18.617
I hope it's not
too much for him.

01:23:26.668 --> 01:23:28.419
Ah... Where are we?

01:23:28.586 --> 01:23:30.212
It's all right.
Everything's fine.

01:23:30.588 --> 01:23:31.755
[GROANING]

01:23:31.923 --> 01:23:34.341
Shh, shh, shh.
Let me take your temperature.

01:23:37.053 --> 01:23:38.679
Come on.

01:23:38.847 --> 01:23:40.764
[PASSENGERS MURMURING]

01:23:47.439 --> 01:23:49.940
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLARlNG]

01:24:00.201 --> 01:24:02.202
[BRAKES SQUEALING]

01:24:07.375 --> 01:24:09.668
Be mindful of these steps.

01:24:22.932 --> 01:24:25.684
SASHA: We've come
to the end of the world.

01:24:48.541 --> 01:24:50.250
This is the stationmaster.

01:24:50.418 --> 01:24:53.128
He's very kind. He said
we may have his home
for as long as we want it.

01:24:53.296 --> 01:24:55.923
There are no inns nearby,
so we are lucky.

01:24:56.091 --> 01:24:58.258
Yes, very lucky.
Yes.

01:24:58.426 --> 01:25:00.511
You'll be comfortable
here, Papa.

01:25:00.678 --> 01:25:04.556
The rest of us, we'll find cots,
or sleep in the station.

01:25:04.724 --> 01:25:06.100
TOLSTOY:
And then we'll be on our way.

01:25:06.267 --> 01:25:10.187
SASHA:
Yes. Yes, Papa.
We'll be on our way.

01:25:11.189 --> 01:25:13.190
[♪♪♪]

01:25:17.487 --> 01:25:18.529
Excuse me?

01:25:18.696 --> 01:25:19.947
[KNOCKS ON WINDOW]

01:25:20.490 --> 01:25:22.199
I'd like to send
a telegram, please.

01:25:23.618 --> 01:25:25.077
Uh...

01:25:25.245 --> 01:25:27.037
At Astapovo. Stop.

01:25:28.581 --> 01:25:31.416
Tolstoy ill. Stop.

01:25:32.669 --> 01:25:33.710
Temperature high.

01:25:34.546 --> 01:25:38.423
You can send it to Countess Sofya
Andreyevna Tolstoya,

01:25:38.591 --> 01:25:41.552
Yasnaya Polyana, Tula Province.

01:25:41.719 --> 01:25:45.305
SOFYA [WHISPERING]:
Please come back.
Please come back.

01:25:57.068 --> 01:25:59.903
DUSHAN:
Concern for Lev Nikolayevich's
health has been expressed

01:26:00.071 --> 01:26:03.073
by people as diverse as
Mr. Henry James

01:26:03.241 --> 01:26:05.159
and Mr. Joseph Conrad.

01:26:05.326 --> 01:26:09.079
Lev Nikolayevich's
temperature currently stands
at 40 degrees Celsius.

01:26:09.247 --> 01:26:11.248
That is 1 04 degrees
Fahrenheit.

01:26:11.416 --> 01:26:14.751
His blood pressure,
which is hypertonic,
is 1 80 over 1 00.

01:26:14.919 --> 01:26:16.712
However, it should be added,

01:26:16.880 --> 01:26:19.006
Lev Nikolayevich's manner

01:26:19.174 --> 01:26:20.757
and mental acuity
CHERTKOV: Bulgakov!

01:26:20.925 --> 01:26:22.801
is as great as ever.

01:26:23.845 --> 01:26:25.679
Where is he? Take me to him.
This way.

01:26:25.847 --> 01:26:28.432
He left. lt's astonishing.
He actually finally left.

01:26:28.600 --> 01:26:32.603
He was very sick, too sick to travel.
It's a triumph for the movement.

01:26:34.856 --> 01:26:36.315
[SNORING]

01:26:36.482 --> 01:26:38.066
[DOOR OPENS]

01:26:43.865 --> 01:26:45.949
CHERTKOV:
He looks so small.

01:26:46.951 --> 01:26:48.619
Papa.

01:26:50.622 --> 01:26:52.623
Oh, it's you.

01:26:53.333 --> 01:26:56.293
My dear friend,

01:26:56.461 --> 01:26:58.587
what is all of this?

01:26:58.755 --> 01:27:01.882
Well, l needed
to see you.

01:27:03.259 --> 01:27:04.509
Thank you.

01:27:04.677 --> 01:27:05.928
[COUGHlNG]

01:27:06.095 --> 01:27:08.305
We have so much to do.

01:27:10.308 --> 01:27:12.684
Have you seen Sofya?

01:27:13.394 --> 01:27:15.479
I've made a point not to.

01:27:16.147 --> 01:27:17.814
TOLSTOY:
She'll come.

01:27:17.982 --> 01:27:21.360
I don't know when she'll come,
but she'll come. I know that.

01:27:21.527 --> 01:27:24.446
And we'll be ready.
Ready for what?

01:27:28.076 --> 01:27:30.661
I'm sorry, but I'm afraid
it's time for your enema.

01:27:30.828 --> 01:27:32.746
Don't apologize,
my friend.

01:27:32.914 --> 01:27:35.374
Your enemas
have become the
news of the world.

01:27:35.541 --> 01:27:37.501
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

01:27:39.462 --> 01:27:41.463
[♪♪♪]

01:28:15.206 --> 01:28:17.207
[SNORES]

01:28:27.260 --> 01:28:28.635
[TYPEWRlTERS CLACKlNG]

01:28:28.803 --> 01:28:32.222
REPORTER 1 :
My only concern is getting
the copy back to London in time.

01:28:32.390 --> 01:28:33.974
Good morning, gentlemen.

01:28:34.142 --> 01:28:36.143
[CROWD CHATTERlNG]

01:28:38.146 --> 01:28:40.397
DUSHAN:
I'm sure you will all be
as relieved as I am

01:28:40.565 --> 01:28:45.068
that Lev Nikolayevich slept
a relatively peaceful night.

01:28:45.862 --> 01:28:49.406
His temperature remains
40 degrees Celsius.

01:28:49.574 --> 01:28:51.742
And his blood pressure
is also hypertonic.

01:28:51.909 --> 01:28:53.827
That having been said, however,

01:28:54.287 --> 01:28:57.998
his mind remains agile
and full of fortitude.

01:28:58.166 --> 01:29:00.709
REPORTER 2: lt's the countess.
Of course, we have to remember...

01:29:00.877 --> 01:29:02.544
REPORTER 3: ls she here?
REPORTER 4: lt's the countess.

01:29:02.712 --> 01:29:05.047
WOMAN: Let's see.
REPORTER 5: Where is she?

01:29:05.214 --> 01:29:08.258
REPORTER 6: lt's the countess!
REPORTER 7: Which car is it?

01:29:08.426 --> 01:29:10.844
[CROWD CLAMORING]

01:29:27.362 --> 01:29:29.738
REPORTER 8: The Countess!
REPORTER 9: There she is.

01:29:30.698 --> 01:29:32.407
REPORTER 1 0:
Countess Sofya.

01:29:34.243 --> 01:29:35.535
SASHA:
She's coming this way.

01:29:35.703 --> 01:29:39.247
Not before she
stops to tell them lies,
catalog my atrocities.

01:29:39.415 --> 01:29:41.416
Let me talk to her.

01:29:41.876 --> 01:29:43.460
I want to see my husband.

01:29:44.128 --> 01:29:45.379
Yes.

01:29:45.546 --> 01:29:46.713
I'll, um...

01:29:47.423 --> 01:29:49.466
I want to see him now!

01:29:49.634 --> 01:29:51.635
VALENTIN:
Countess! Countess!

01:29:51.803 --> 01:29:54.638
Oh, Valentin.
I want to see him, please.

01:29:54.806 --> 01:29:56.848
I'm not sure now
is the right time, countess.

01:29:57.016 --> 01:29:59.559
Yes, it is.
It's the right time for me.

01:29:59.727 --> 01:30:01.645
REPORTER 1 1 :
Have you had any contact?

01:30:03.272 --> 01:30:06.149
VALENTIN:
It might be a better idea, countess,
I really think, if you just waited...

01:30:06.317 --> 01:30:07.651
REPORTER 1 2:
He only left because of you.

01:30:07.819 --> 01:30:09.152
REPORTER 1 3:
Countess!

01:30:17.036 --> 01:30:18.328
I want to see my husband.

01:30:18.496 --> 01:30:20.622
He's too weak
to see you now, Mother.

01:30:20.790 --> 01:30:23.708
He's not too weak to see you.
Not too weak to see that-- Pfft.

01:30:23.876 --> 01:30:26.336
Do you really want
to do this here?

01:30:26.504 --> 01:30:31.133
So l am the leper outside
the gate, while he sleeps
with the devil himself.

01:30:31.300 --> 01:30:35.011
Chertkov is here
because Father
asked him to be here.

01:30:36.597 --> 01:30:39.975
Is that true?
Yes.

01:30:43.187 --> 01:30:46.690
Well, did you tell him that
I nearly drowned in the pond?

01:30:47.483 --> 01:30:50.485
We didn't need to.
It's been in all the papers.

01:30:50.653 --> 01:30:52.863
Please, let me take you back.
What did he say?

01:30:54.240 --> 01:30:57.576
He said that if you killed
yourself, he'd be upset.

01:30:59.203 --> 01:31:03.457
He'd be upset?
Horribly upset.

01:31:04.333 --> 01:31:06.626
But he could not have
acted other than he did.

01:31:06.794 --> 01:31:08.462
I want to see him.

01:31:10.548 --> 01:31:12.966
He's my husband.
He's not your husband.

01:31:13.134 --> 01:31:14.217
Oh, you're unbearable.

01:31:14.385 --> 01:31:17.554
And you are a stone-hearted
bitch of a daughter.

01:31:17.722 --> 01:31:20.015
[CROWD GASPS
AND CHUCKLES]

01:31:20.224 --> 01:31:21.558
I lost five children!

01:31:21.726 --> 01:31:23.768
Why couldn't one of them
have been you?

01:31:23.936 --> 01:31:25.520
[CROWD GASPS]

01:31:25.688 --> 01:31:27.647
REPORTER 14:
Did she just say that?

01:31:28.691 --> 01:31:30.650
[WHlSPERS]
Are you finished?

01:31:31.235 --> 01:31:33.320
[SCRIBBLING]

01:31:33.488 --> 01:31:35.822
[♪♪♪]

01:31:37.325 --> 01:31:39.326
Valentin, would you
take me back, please?

01:31:39.494 --> 01:31:41.244
Yes, of course.

01:31:43.831 --> 01:31:47.250
Please, make way.
Make way. Make way.

01:31:47.418 --> 01:31:49.252
[CROWD CLAMORING]

01:31:49.420 --> 01:31:53.215
I've behaved rather badly, haven't I?
No, countess.

01:31:53.549 --> 01:31:55.300
No, don't worry.

01:33:05.496 --> 01:33:08.623
Here. For you.

01:33:15.840 --> 01:33:18.383
Is this clean?
Of course it's clean.

01:33:18.968 --> 01:33:21.761
[TOLSTOY MOANlNG]

01:33:21.929 --> 01:33:23.930
Dushan,
what's the matter?

01:33:24.181 --> 01:33:26.016
Listen to him.

01:33:26.434 --> 01:33:29.352
I'm supposed to be
a doctor, for God's sake.

01:33:29.645 --> 01:33:31.479
TOLSTOY:
Sofya?

01:33:32.148 --> 01:33:33.773
Sofya?

01:33:33.941 --> 01:33:35.734
DUSHAN:
What is it?

01:33:36.527 --> 01:33:37.861
What is it?

01:33:40.197 --> 01:33:43.074
[MUMBLING]

01:33:43.284 --> 01:33:45.702
She's come, hasn't she?

01:33:46.704 --> 01:33:49.831
She's here.
You're imagining things.

01:33:49.999 --> 01:33:51.207
TOLSTOY:
Sasha!

01:33:52.877 --> 01:33:54.669
Where is your mother?

01:33:55.838 --> 01:33:57.714
CHERTKOV:
She's at home.

01:34:00.217 --> 01:34:03.637
If she wants to see me,
I can't refuse her.

01:34:03.804 --> 01:34:05.430
Yes.

01:34:06.307 --> 01:34:08.475
TOLSTOY:
Is she going to come here?

01:34:09.477 --> 01:34:11.102
I don't...

01:34:11.896 --> 01:34:13.647
There's no way to...

01:34:15.232 --> 01:34:17.734
There's no way to what?

01:34:39.423 --> 01:34:41.591
I'd like to send
another telegram, please.

01:34:43.344 --> 01:34:45.011
At Astapovo. Stop.

01:34:46.806 --> 01:34:49.265
Tolstoy ill. Stop.

01:34:49.433 --> 01:34:51.768
Heartbreaking. Stop.
Please come.

01:34:54.271 --> 01:34:56.272
You can send it to Masha--

01:34:57.108 --> 01:34:58.775
Maria Filipovna Melinova.

01:35:03.280 --> 01:35:05.281
VALENTIN:
You lied to him.

01:35:05.449 --> 01:35:06.950
CHERTKOV:
Keep your voice down.

01:35:07.118 --> 01:35:09.035
VALENTIN:
He wants to see her.
You heard him say it.

01:35:09.912 --> 01:35:12.038
And what exactly do you
think she'll bring him here?

01:35:12.206 --> 01:35:14.499
I don't know. They've been
married for 48 years.

01:35:14.709 --> 01:35:17.377
I'll tell you exactly
what she'll bring.
Vanity, fuss and noise.

01:35:17.545 --> 01:35:18.795
She promised me
she would not--

01:35:18.963 --> 01:35:20.839
Promised you what?
What, what?

01:35:21.006 --> 01:35:22.966
You've seen her at
close quarters, my boy.

01:35:23.134 --> 01:35:26.469
Do you really think that she's
capable of restraining herself
from acting like a madwoman?

01:35:26.637 --> 01:35:28.680
They have a whole life together.
Why do you have to deny that?

01:35:28.848 --> 01:35:31.391
You have become a victim
of her romantic nonsense.

01:35:32.268 --> 01:35:35.645
And you willfully forget
that she wants to destroy
everything we do.

01:35:35.813 --> 01:35:37.897
She travels here with that
unctuous little priest.

01:35:38.065 --> 01:35:41.484
We'll keep the priest away.
These people are vultures, Valentin.

01:35:41.652 --> 01:35:44.154
And they wait to descend
till the very last moment

01:35:44.321 --> 01:35:46.114
to welcome him back
to the Church.

01:35:46.282 --> 01:35:48.450
This is their fantasy.
Keep the priest away.

01:35:48.617 --> 01:35:49.993
A deathbed recantation.

01:35:50.161 --> 01:35:54.622
Do you have any idea
the damage that that will do?

01:35:54.790 --> 01:35:56.499
Everything that he has
dreamed of,

01:35:56.667 --> 01:36:02.338
everything that we have
worked for will be gone.

01:36:02.840 --> 01:36:06.009
A simple, noble death

01:36:06.177 --> 01:36:08.344
is what we want.

01:36:09.054 --> 01:36:11.264
That's what he wants.

01:36:14.101 --> 01:36:16.603
No, you want
to create an icon.

01:36:17.188 --> 01:36:20.482
And you want people
to kneel in front of an
image that you create.

01:36:20.649 --> 01:36:22.108
But he doesn't want that.

01:36:22.276 --> 01:36:25.653
He never has wanted that.
It'll give him no peace.

01:36:27.615 --> 01:36:30.533
He wants to see her.
Let her come.

01:36:32.661 --> 01:36:36.039
I will do everything in
my power to prevent that.

01:36:36.207 --> 01:36:37.707
[GRUNTS]

01:36:38.876 --> 01:36:40.543
That image
you want to create,

01:36:42.505 --> 01:36:44.881
it's going to look
more like you than him.

01:36:45.049 --> 01:36:47.383
[♪♪♪]

01:37:21.794 --> 01:37:24.796
[PEOPLE CHATTERlNG
AND LAUGHlNG]

01:37:48.779 --> 01:37:50.405
DUSHAN:
Valentin?

01:37:59.874 --> 01:38:02.500
[GROANING]

01:38:07.840 --> 01:38:10.300
It can't be right.
His fever is down.

01:38:10.467 --> 01:38:11.968
Yes.

01:38:12.136 --> 01:38:13.469
But, uh...

01:38:14.096 --> 01:38:17.974
his pulse,
you see, it's...

01:38:19.476 --> 01:38:20.935
[SOBBING]

01:38:25.733 --> 01:38:27.400
My dear.

01:38:32.156 --> 01:38:34.324
Shall l call her?

01:38:34.700 --> 01:38:37.327
He wouldn't know
who she is anyway.

01:38:37.494 --> 01:38:38.828
Yes.

01:38:43.876 --> 01:38:46.878
[♪♪♪]

01:38:55.179 --> 01:38:57.180
[FOOTSTEPS]

01:39:03.812 --> 01:39:06.022
Bring a coat. It's cold.

01:39:15.407 --> 01:39:19.160
REPORTER:
Countess. Countess, could you
give me some information?

01:39:19.370 --> 01:39:21.287
Countess, is he dying?

01:39:21.956 --> 01:39:23.373
Is he dead?

01:39:26.377 --> 01:39:28.753
[VALENTIN PRAYING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:39:28.963 --> 01:39:30.421
[DOOR OPENS]

01:39:34.718 --> 01:39:38.471
Leovochka!
Leovochka, my darling.

01:39:38.973 --> 01:39:41.224
Oh, my darling,
please forgive me, please!

01:39:41.850 --> 01:39:46.688
I'm a fool. I'm a selfish woman,
but I love you, darling.

01:39:46.855 --> 01:39:49.190
Please believe me.

01:39:49.358 --> 01:39:52.777
Please, please understand me,

01:39:52.945 --> 01:39:55.822
and please forgive my
wickedness and my badness.

01:39:55.990 --> 01:39:57.740
SASHA:
Mother.

01:39:58.617 --> 01:40:00.618
Control yourself.

01:40:00.786 --> 01:40:04.205
Am l shouting?
You have to control yourself.

01:40:07.209 --> 01:40:08.876
Yes.

01:40:09.044 --> 01:40:10.962
Yes, l will.

01:40:22.766 --> 01:40:25.393
[♪♪♪]

01:40:26.937 --> 01:40:30.857
You don't speak, but I hear you.

01:40:32.359 --> 01:40:34.944
Do you love me, Leovochka?

01:40:40.784 --> 01:40:43.619
I never stopped,
my little bird.

01:40:47.124 --> 01:40:49.459
And you will never stop?

01:40:51.420 --> 01:40:52.837
No.

01:40:53.255 --> 01:40:54.797
Never.

01:40:57.676 --> 01:40:59.761
Nor ever leave me again?

01:41:02.806 --> 01:41:06.642
No, never again.

01:41:07.519 --> 01:41:11.230
Good.

01:41:13.025 --> 01:41:14.067
Let's go home.

01:41:46.308 --> 01:41:48.184
[GASPING]

01:41:50.020 --> 01:41:52.021
First cessation.

01:42:04.284 --> 01:42:06.452
Second cessation.

01:42:12.292 --> 01:42:13.626
[SOBBING]

01:42:25.139 --> 01:42:27.807
SOFYA:
Shh. Shh.

01:42:27.975 --> 01:42:29.976
[♪♪♪]

01:42:56.170 --> 01:43:00.590
DUSHAN:
Ten minutes after 6
in the morning,

01:43:02.426 --> 01:43:04.969
a great soul passed
from our world.

01:43:06.930 --> 01:43:10.099
Lev Nikolayevich Tolstoy...

01:43:10.267 --> 01:43:13.060
[CROWD SlNGING
IN FORElGN LANGUAGE]

01:43:58.398 --> 01:44:00.149
[♪♪♪]

01:44:06.990 --> 01:44:08.532
Masha.

01:44:15.999 --> 01:44:19.502
Masha. Oh, Masha.

01:44:21.672 --> 01:44:24.423
I'm sorry, but he is gone.
I know.

01:44:28.178 --> 01:44:30.680
But I came for you, Valya.

01:44:32.266 --> 01:44:33.683
I came for you too.

01:45:23.692 --> 01:45:26.193
WOMAN 1 :
God go with you,
Sofya Andreyevna.

01:45:26.361 --> 01:45:28.279
MAN:
God bless you!

01:45:30.615 --> 01:45:33.284
WOMAN 2:
We'll pray for you, countess!

01:47:35.782 --> 01:49:15.005
[♪♪♪]
